29/* generate asts for calling an io routine; must be performed in the
30 * the following order:
31 * begin_io_call()
32 * add_io_arg() [zero or more calls]
33 * end_io_call() [optional assignment of function]
34 */
35
36static struct { /* record info for begin_io_call - end_io_call */
37 int ast;
38 int ast_type;
39 int std;
40} io_call;
41
42/*-------- define data structures and macros local to this file: --------*/
43
44/* define macros used to access table the I/O parameter table, "pt".
45 * All of the macros that can be used in the INQUIRE statement are at
46 * the beginning (their values range from 0 .. PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL).
47 * These are in the order specified by the fio_inquire routine in the
48 * HPF Execution Environment spec. and only include those which are passed
49 * as arguments. Note that ERR is not passed to fio_inquire.
50 *
51 * N O T E: The static array of struct, pt, is initialized the names of
52 * these parameters. If changes are made to the PT_ macros,
53 * R E M E M B E R to change ptname.
54 */
55#define PT_UNIT 0
56#define PT_FILE 1
57#define PT_IOSTAT 2
58#define PT_EXIST 3
59#define PT_OPENED 4
60#define PT_NUMBER 5
61#define PT_NAMED 6
62#define PT_NAME 7
63#define PT_ACCESS 8
64#define PT_SEQUENTIAL 9
65#define PT_DIRECT 10
66#define PT_FORM 11
67#define PT_FORMATTED 12
68#define PT_UNFORMATTED 13
69#define PT_RECL 14
70#define PT_NEXTREC 15
71#define PT_BLANK 16
72#define PT_POSITION 17
73#define PT_ACTION 18
74#define PT_READ 19
75#define PT_WRITE 20
76#define PT_READWRITE 21
77#define PT_DELIM 22
78#define PT_PAD 23
79#define PT_ID 24
80#define PT_PENDING 25
81#define PT_POS 26
82#define PT_SIZE 27
83#define PT_ASYNCHRONOUS 28
84#define PT_DECIMAL 29
85#define PT_ENCODING 30
86#define PT_SIGN 31
87#define PT_STREAM 32
88#define PT_ROUND 33
89/* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
90 * end of INQUIRE parameters: make sure that PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL is set
91 * to the last inquire value.
92 * Values <= including PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VALf95 are f95 inquire specifiers
93 * values > PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VALf95 and <= PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL are the new
94 * f2003 inquire specifiers.
95 *
96 * PT_IOLENGTH is only present since certain utility functions, such as
97 * chk_var, require a 'pt' argument.
98 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * */
99#define PT_DISPOSE 34
100#define PT_END 35
101#define PT_ERR 36
102#define PT_FMT 37
103#define PT_NML 38
104#define PT_REC 39
105#define PT_STATUS 40
106#define PT_ADVANCE 41
107#define PT_EOR 42
108#define PT_IOLENGTH 43
109#define PT_CONVERT 44
110#define PT_SHARED 45
111#define PT_IOMSG 46
112#define PT_NEWUNIT 47
113
114#define PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VALf95 PT_PAD
115#define PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL 33
116#define PT_MAXV 47
117
118/*
119 * define bit flag for each I/O statement. Used for checking
120 * illegal cases of I/O keyword specifiers.
121 */
122#define BT_ACCEPT 0x00001
123#define BT_BKSPACE 0x00002
124#define BT_CLOSE 0x00004
125#define BT_DECODE 0x00008
126#define BT_ENCODE 0x00010
127#define BT_ENDFILE 0x00020
128#define BT_INQUIRE 0x00040
129#define BT_OPEN 0x00080
130#define BT_PRINT 0x00100
131#define BT_READ 0x00200
132#define BT_REWIND 0x00400
133#define BT_WRITE 0x00800
134#define BT_WAIT 0x01000
135#define BT_FLUSH 0x02000
136
137/* define macros for the edit descriptors */
138#define PUT(n) (_put((INT)(n), DT_INT))

140/* define format type macros: */
141typedef enum {
142 FT_UNFORMATTED = 1,
143 FT_LIST_DIRECTED = 2,
144 FT_ENCODED = 3,
145 FT_CHARACTER = 4,
146 FT_NML = 5,
147 FT_FMTSTR = 6,
148 FT_LAST = 7
149} FormatType;
150
151/* Array indexed by [is_read][<format type from above>] */
152static int functype[2][FT_LAST] = {
153 {DT_IO_FWRITE, DT_IO_UWRITE, DT_IO_FWRITE, DT_IO_FWRITE, DT_IO_FWRITE,
154 DT_IO_FWRITE, DT_IO_FWRITE},
155 {DT_IO_FREAD, DT_IO_UREAD, DT_IO_FREAD, DT_IO_FREAD, DT_IO_FREAD,
156 DT_IO_FREAD, DT_IO_FREAD}};

158/* miscellaneous macros: */
159
160#define DEFAULT_UNIT (is_read ? 5 : 6)
161#define IOERR(n) errsev(n)
162#define IOERR2(n, s) error(n, 3, gbl.lineno, s, CNULL)
163#define ERR170(s) error(170, 2, gbl.lineno, s, CNULL)
164#define ERR204(s1, s2) error(204, 3, gbl.lineno, s1, s2)

166#define PTV(d) pt[d].val
167#define PT_CHECK(a, b) \
168 if (PTV(a) == 0) \
169 PTV(a) = b
170#define PTS(a) pt[a].set
171#define PT_SET(a) PTS(a) = 1
172#define PTVARREF(a) pt[a].varref
173#define PT_VARREF(a, v) PTVARREF(a) = (v)
174#define PTTMPUSED(a) pt[a].tmp_in_use
175#define PT_TMPUSED(a, v) (pt[a].tmp_in_use = (v))
176#define PTARG(a) \
177 (PTVARREF(a) && PTVARREF(a) != 1 ? PT_TMPUSED(a, 1), PTV(a) : PTV(a))
178#define PTNAME(a) pt[a].name
179#define PTSTMT(a) pt[a].stmt
180#define UNIT_CHECK \
181 if (PTV(PT_UNIT) == 0) \
182 IOERR(200)

201static struct pt_tag { /* parameter table for I/O statements */
202 int val; /* pointer to AST of I/O keyword specifier, except
203 * for a keyword specifier for a label, in which
204 * case val is the sptr of the label.
205 */
206 int set;
207 int varref; /* zero ==> io specifier is not a variable,
208 * non-zero ==> io specifier is a variable reference,
209 * where
210 * the value 1 means that the variable is
211 * being used directly, and any other
212 * non zero value implies that a temp
213 * value is being used in which case
214 * 1) val contains the ast referencing
215 * the temp
216 * 2) and varref (this field) contains
217 * the ast referencing the original
218 * variable.
219 */
220 int tmp_in_use; /* 1==>a tmp is being used in the current call (see above) */
221 const char *name;
222 int stmt; /* I/O stmts which may use parameter/keyword */
223} pt[PT_MAXV + 1] = {
224 {0, 0, 0, 0, "UNIT",
225 BT_BKSPACE | BT_CLOSE | BT_ENDFILE | BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_READ |
226 BT_REWIND | BT_WRITE | BT_WAIT | BT_FLUSH},
227 {0, 0, 0, 0, "FILE", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
228 {0, 0, 0, 0, "IOSTAT",
229 BT_BKSPACE | BT_CLOSE | BT_DECODE | BT_ENCODE | BT_ENDFILE | BT_INQUIRE |
230 BT_OPEN | BT_READ | BT_REWIND | BT_WRITE | BT_WAIT | BT_FLUSH},
231 {0, 0, 0, 0, "EXIST", BT_INQUIRE},
232 {0, 0, 0, 0, "OPENED", BT_INQUIRE},
233 {0, 0, 0, 0, "NUMBER", BT_INQUIRE},
234 {0, 0, 0, 0, "NAMED", BT_INQUIRE},
235 {0, 0, 0, 0, "NAME", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
236 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ACCESS", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
237 {0, 0, 0, 0, "SEQUENTIAL", BT_INQUIRE},
238 {0, 0, 0, 0, "DIRECT", BT_INQUIRE},
239 {0, 0, 0, 0, "FORM", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
240 {0, 0, 0, 0, "FORMATTED", BT_INQUIRE},
241 {0, 0, 0, 0, "UNFORMATTED", BT_INQUIRE},
242 {0, 0, 0, 0, "RECL", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
243 {0, 0, 0, 0, "NEXTREC", BT_INQUIRE},
244 {0, 0, 0, 0, "BLANK", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_READ},
245 {0, 0, 0, 0, "POSITION", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
246 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ACTION", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
247 {0, 0, 0, 0, "READ", BT_INQUIRE},
248 {0, 0, 0, 0, "WRITE", BT_INQUIRE},
249 {0, 0, 0, 0, "READWRITE", BT_INQUIRE},
250 {0, 0, 0, 0, "DELIM", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_WRITE},
251 {0, 0, 0, 0, "PAD", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_READ},
252 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ID", BT_INQUIRE | BT_READ | BT_WRITE | BT_WAIT},
253 {0, 0, 0, 0, "PENDING", BT_INQUIRE},
254 {0, 0, 0, 0, "POS", BT_INQUIRE | BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
255 {0, 0, 0, 0, "SIZE", BT_INQUIRE | BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
256 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ASYNCHRONOUS", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
257 {0, 0, 0, 0, "DECIMAL", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
258 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ENCODING", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN},
259 {0, 0, 0, 0, "SIGN", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_WRITE},
260 {0, 0, 0, 0, "STREAM", BT_INQUIRE},
261 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ROUND", BT_INQUIRE | BT_OPEN | BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
262 {0, 0, 0, 0, "DISPOSE", BT_CLOSE | BT_OPEN},
263 {0, 0, 0, 0, "END", BT_READ | BT_WAIT},
264 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ERR",
265 BT_BKSPACE | BT_CLOSE | BT_DECODE | BT_ENCODE | BT_ENDFILE | BT_INQUIRE |
266 BT_OPEN | BT_READ | BT_REWIND | BT_WRITE | BT_WAIT | BT_FLUSH},
267 {0, 0, 0, 0, "FMT", BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
268 {0, 0, 0, 0, "NML", BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
269 {0, 0, 0, 0, "REC", BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
270 {0, 0, 0, 0, "STATUS", BT_CLOSE | BT_OPEN},
271 {0, 0, 0, 0, "ADVANCE", BT_READ | BT_WRITE},
272 {0, 0, 0, 0, "EOR", BT_READ | BT_WAIT},
273 {0, 0, 0, 0, "IOLENGTH", BT_INQUIRE},
274 {0, 0, 0, 0, "CONVERT", BT_OPEN},
275 {0, 0, 0, 0, "SHARED", BT_OPEN},
276 {0, 0, 0, 0, "IOMSG",
277 BT_BKSPACE | BT_CLOSE | BT_DECODE | BT_ENCODE | BT_ENDFILE | BT_INQUIRE |

315#define BITV_IOSTAT 0x01

327#define BYTE_SWAPPED_IO (XBIT(125, 0x2) != 0)
328#define LARGE_ARRAY (XBIT(68, 1) != 0)

330/* Selectable unfomatted i/o routines:
331 * Indexed by:
332 * 1) LARGE_ARRAY_IDX
333 *
334 * 2) 0 - normal unformatted i/o (file format matches native byte order)
335 * 1 - byte-swapped unf i/o (file format is reversed from native byte order).
336 * 2 - byte read/write
337 *
338 * '-x 125 2' is used to select one of the first two entries; aggregate
339 * unformatted i/o selects the third entry.
340 */
341
342#define BYTE_SWAPPED_IO_IDX ((BYTE_SWAPPED_IO) ? 1 : 0)
343#define LARGE_ARRAY_IDX ((LARGE_ARRAY) ? 1 : 0)
344#define BYTE_RW_IDX 2

349 FtnRtlEnum write;
350 FtnRtlEnum end;
351} UnformattedRtns;

466/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
467
468/** \brief Semantic analysis of IO statements.
469 \param rednum reduction number
470 \param top top of stack after reduction
471 */
472void
473semantio(int rednum, SST *top)
474{
475 int sptr, i, iofunc;
476 int len;
477 int dtype;
478 int dum;
479 ADSC *ad;
480 SST *stkptr, *e1;
481 IOL *iolptr;
482 IOL *dobegin, *doend;
483 DOINFO *doinfo;
484 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn;
485 int ast;
486 int count;
487 int ast1, ast2, ast3;
488 int dim; /* dimension # of the index variable */
489 int asd; /* array subscript descriptor */
490 int subs[7];
491 int numdim;
492 int sptr1;
493 int nelems;
494 int last_inquire_val;
495 ITEM *itemp;
496 char *strptr;
497 LOGICAL needDescr;
498
499 switch (rednum) {
500
501 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
502 /*
503 * <null> ::=
504 */
505 case NULL1:
506 /*
507 * this reduction is made at the beginning of any I/O statement
508 * not involving the transfer of data. It is used to initialize for
509 * the processing of these statements.
510 */
511 no_rw = TRUE;
512 goto io_shared;
513
514 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
515 /*
516 * <write> ::=
517 */
518 case WRITE1:
519 /*
520 * this reduction is made at the beginning of any I/O statement
521 * performing output. It is used to initialize for the processing
522 * of these statements.
523 */
524 is_read = FALSE;
525 goto rw_init;
526
527 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
528 /*
529 * <read> ::=
530 */
531 case READ1:
532 /*
533 * this reduction is made at the beginning of any I/O statement
534 * performing input. It is used to initialize for the processing
535 * of these statements.
536 */
537 is_read = TRUE;
538 rw_init:
539 sem.io_stmt = TRUE;
540 fmttyp = FT_UNFORMATTED;
541 intern = FALSE;
542 no_rw = FALSE;
543 print_star = FALSE;
544 unit_star = FALSE;
545
546 /* shared entry for all io statements except bufferin/bufferout */
547
548 io_shared:
549 set_io_sc();
550 bitv = 0;
551 for (i = 0; i <= PT_MAXV; i++) {
552 PTV(i) = 0;
553 PTS(i) = 0;
554 PTVARREF(i) = 0;
555 PT_TMPUSED(i, 0);
556 }
557 if (flg.smp || flg.accmp || XBIT(125, 0x1)) {
558 /* begin i/o critical section */
559 if (flg.smp || flg.accmp)
560 sptr = sym_mkfunc_nodesc("_mp_bcs_nest", DT_NONE);
561 else
562 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_begin, DT_NONE, 0);
563 (void)begin_io_call(A_CALL, sptr, 0);
564 ast = end_io_call();
565 STD_LINENO(io_call.std) = gbl.lineno;
566 /*
567 * if an I/O statement is labeled, ensure that the first 'statement'
568 * generated is labeled.
569 */
570 if (scn.currlab && !DEFDG(scn.currlab)) {
571 STD_LABEL(io_call.std) = scn.currlab;
572 DEFDP(scn.currlab, 1);
573 }
574 }
575 /*
576 * Create a character variable which is data initialized with
577 * the name of the source file if character constants can't be
578 * passed to RTE_loc(). Certain systems (hp) may place character
579 * constants on the stack, in which case the run-time or generated
580 * code can't stash away the address of the constant.
581 */
582 sptr = getstring(gbl.curr_file, strlen(gbl.curr_file));
583 if (!XBIT(49, 0x100000))
584 ast1 = mk_cnst(sptr);
585 else {
586 sptr1 = getcctmp_sc('t', sptr, ST_UNKNOWN, DTYPEG(sptr), io_sc);
587 if (STYPEG(sptr1) == ST_UNKNOWN) {
588 STYPEP(sptr1, ST_VAR);
589 DINITP(sptr1, 1);
590 if (SCG(sptr1) != SC_NONE)
591 sym_is_refd(sptr1);
592 dinit_put(DINIT_LOC, sptr1);
593 dinit_put(DINIT_STR, (INT)sptr);
594 dinit_put(DINIT_END, (INT)0);
595 }
596 ast1 = mk_id(sptr1);
597 }
598 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_src_info03a, DT_NONE, 0);
599 (void)begin_io_call(A_CALL, sptr, 2);
600 (void)add_io_arg(mk_cval((INT)gbl.lineno, DT_INT));
601 (void)add_io_arg(ast1);
602 ast = end_io_call();
603 STD_LINENO(io_call.std) = gbl.lineno;
604 /*
605 * if an I/O statement is labeled, ensure that the first 'statement'
606 * generated is labeled.
607 */
608 if (!XBIT(125, 0x1) && !flg.smp && !flg.accmp && scn.currlab &&
609 !DEFDG(scn.currlab)) {
610 STD_LABEL(io_call.std) = scn.currlab;
611 DEFDP(scn.currlab, 1);
612 }
613
614 iolist = 0;
615 noparens = FALSE;
616 external_io = FALSE;
617 nondevice_io = FALSE;
618 open03 = FALSE;
619 rw03 = FALSE;
620 break;
621
622 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
623 /*
624 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> BACKSPACE <unit info> |
625 */
626 case IO_STMT1:
627 (void)misc_io_checks("BACKSPACE");
628 iomsg_check();
629 kwd_errchk(BT_BKSPACE);
630 if (BYTE_SWAPPED_IO)
631 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_swbackspace; /* byte swap backspace */
632 else
633 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_backspace;
634 goto rewind_shared;
635 /*
636 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> ENDFILE <unit info> |
637 */
638 case IO_STMT2:
639 (void)misc_io_checks("ENDFILE");
640 iomsg_check();
641 kwd_errchk(BT_ENDFILE);
642 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_endfile;
643 goto rewind_shared;
644 /*
645 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> REWIND <unit info> |
646 */
647 case IO_STMT3:
648 (void)misc_io_checks("REWIND");
649 iomsg_check();
650 kwd_errchk(BT_REWIND);
651 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_rewind;
652 rewind_shared:
653 sptr = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, 0);
654 UNIT_CHECK;
655 fix_iostat();
656 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 3);
657 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_UNIT));
658 (void)add_io_arg(mk_cval(bitv, DT_INT));
659 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_IOSTAT));
660 ast = end_io_call();
661 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
662 external_io = TRUE;
663 nondevice_io = TRUE;
664 goto end_IO_STMT;
665 /*
666 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> CLOSE <iolp> <spec list> ) |
667 */
668 case IO_STMT4:
669 (void)misc_io_checks("CLOSE");
670 iomsg_check();
671 UNIT_CHECK;
672 kwd_errchk(BT_CLOSE);
673 if (PTV(PT_STATUS)) {
674 if (PTV(PT_DISPOSE))
675 IOERR2(202, "STATUS and DISPOSE in CLOSE");
676 } else
677 PTV(PT_STATUS) = PTV(PT_DISPOSE);
678 PT_CHECK(PT_STATUS, astb.ptr0c);
679 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_closea, DT_INT, 0);
680 fix_iostat();
681 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 4);
682 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_UNIT));
683 (void)add_io_arg(mk_cval(bitv, DT_INT));
684 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_IOSTAT));
685 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_STATUS));
686 ast = end_io_call();
687 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
688 external_io = TRUE;
689 nondevice_io = TRUE;
690 goto end_IO_STMT;
691 /*
692 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> OPEN <iolp> <spec list> ) |
693 */
694 case IO_STMT5:
695 (void)misc_io_checks("OPEN");
696 iomsg_check();
697 UNIT_CHECK;
698 newunit_check();
699 kwd_errchk(BT_OPEN);
700 PT_CHECK(PT_ACCESS, astb.ptr0c);
701 PT_CHECK(PT_ACTION, astb.ptr0c);
702 PT_CHECK(PT_BLANK, astb.ptr0c);
703 PT_CHECK(PT_DELIM, astb.ptr0c);
704 PT_CHECK(PT_FORM, astb.ptr0c);
705 fix_iostat();
706 PT_CHECK(PT_PAD, astb.ptr0c);
707 PT_CHECK(PT_POSITION, astb.ptr0c);
708 PT_CHECK(PT_RECL, astb.ptr0);
709 PT_CHECK(PT_STATUS, astb.ptr0c);
710 PT_CHECK(PT_FILE, astb.ptr0c);
711 PT_CHECK(PT_DISPOSE, astb.ptr0c);
712
713 if (PTS(PT_NEWUNIT)) {
714 sptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_f90io_get_newunit), DT_INT);
715 INDEPP(sptr, 1);
716 TYPDP(sptr, 1);
717 INTERNALP(sptr, 0);
718
719 ast = mk_func_node(A_FUNC, mk_id(sptr), 0, 0);
720 ast = mk_assn_stmt(PTV(PT_NEWUNIT), ast, A_DTYPEG(PTV(PT_NEWUNIT)));
721 add_stmt_after(ast, io_call.std);
722 if (A_DTYPEG(PTV(PT_NEWUNIT)) != DT_INT) {
723 PTV(PT_UNIT) = mk_convert(PTV(PT_NEWUNIT), DT_INT);
724 }
725 }
726
727 if (PTS(PT_FILE) && PTS(PT_NAME))
728 IOERR2(202, "FILE and NAME in OPEN");
729
730 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_open2003a, DT_INT, 0);
731 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 14);
732 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_UNIT));
733 (void)add_io_arg(mk_cval(bitv, DT_INT));
734 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_ACCESS));
735 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_ACTION));
736 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_BLANK));
737 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_DELIM));
738
739 /* on open statement, FILE and NAME are the same. code previously
740 only set PT_FILE, but this created incorrect error messages */
741 if (PTV(PT_NAME))
742 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_NAME));
743 else
744 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_FILE));
745 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_FORM));
746 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_IOSTAT));
747 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_PAD));
748 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_POSITION));
749 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_RECL));
750 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_STATUS));
751 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_DISPOSE));
752 ast = end_io_call();
753 if (PTV(PT_CONVERT)) {
754 /* ast is an A_ASN of the form
755 * z_io = ...open(...)
756 */
757 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_open_cvta, DT_INT, 0);
758 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 2);
759 (void)add_io_arg(A_DESTG(ast));
760 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_CONVERT));
761 ast = end_io_call();
762 }
763 if (PTV(PT_SHARED)) {
764 /* ast is an A_ASN of the form
765 * z_io = ...open(...)
766 */
767 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_open_sharea, DT_INT, 0);
768 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 2);
769 (void)add_io_arg(A_DESTG(ast));
770 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_SHARED));
771 ast = end_io_call();
772 }
773 if (PTV(PT_ASYNCHRONOUS)) {
774 /* ast is an A_ASN of the form
775 * z_io = ...open(...)
776 */
777 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_open_asynca, DT_INT, 0);
778 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 2);
779 (void)add_io_arg(A_DESTG(ast));
780 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_ASYNCHRONOUS));
781 ast = end_io_call();
782 }
783 if (open03) {
784 /* ast is an A_ASN of the form
785 * z_io = ...open(...)
786 */
787 PT_CHECK(PT_DECIMAL, astb.ptr0c);
788 PT_CHECK(PT_ROUND, astb.ptr0c);
789 PT_CHECK(PT_SIGN, astb.ptr0c);
790 PT_CHECK(PT_ENCODING, astb.ptr0c);
791 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_open03a, DT_INT, 0);
792 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 5);
793 (void)add_io_arg(A_DESTG(ast));
794 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_DECIMAL));
795 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_ROUND));
796 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_SIGN));
797 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_ENCODING));
798 ast = end_io_call();
799 }
800 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
801 external_io = TRUE;
802 nondevice_io = TRUE;
803 goto end_IO_STMT;
804 /*
805 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> INQUIRE <iolp> <spec list> ) |
806 */
807 case IO_STMT6:
808
809 (void)misc_io_checks("INQUIRE");
810 iomsg_check();
811 if (PTV(PT_UNIT)) {
812 if (PTV(PT_FILE))
813 IOERR2(201, "UNIT and FILE used in INQUIRE");
814 PTV(PT_FILE) = astb.ptr0c;
815 } else if (PTV(PT_FILE))
816 PTV(PT_UNIT) = astb.i0;
817 else
818 IOERR(200);
819
820 kwd_errchk(BT_INQUIRE);
821
822 last_inquire_val = PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VALf95;
823 for (i = PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VALf95 + 1; i <= PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL; i++) {
824 if (PTV(i)) {
825 last_inquire_val = PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL;
826 break;
827 }
828 }
829 for (i = 2; i <= last_inquire_val; i++) {
830 switch (i) {
831 case PT_NEXTREC:
832 case PT_NUMBER:
833 case PT_RECL:
834 case PT_SIZE:
835 case PT_IOSTAT:
836 case PT_EXIST:
837 case PT_NAMED:
838 case PT_OPENED:
839 case PT_ID:
840 case PT_PENDING:
841 case PT_POS:
842 PT_CHECK(i, astb.ptr0);
843 break;
844 default:
845 PT_CHECK(i, astb.ptr0c);
846 }
847 }
848
849 if (last_inquire_val < PT_LAST_INQUIRE_VAL) {
850 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_inquire2003a, DT_INT, 0);
851 } else {
852 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_inquire03_2a, DT_INT, 0);
853 }
854 filename_type = 0;
855 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, last_inquire_val + 2);
856 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_UNIT));
857 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_FILE));
858 (void)add_io_arg(mk_cval(bitv, DT_INT));
859 for (i = 2; i <= last_inquire_val; i++)
860 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(i));
861 ast = end_io_call();
862
863 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
864 external_io = TRUE;
865 nondevice_io = TRUE;
866 goto end_IO_STMT;
867 /*
868 * <IO stmt> ::= <write> WRITE <io spec> |
869 */
870 case IO_STMT7:
871 (void)misc_io_checks("WRITE");
872 kwd_errchk(BT_WRITE);
873 external_io = !intern;
874 goto io_end;
875 /*
876 * <IO stmt> ::= <write> WRITE <io spec> <output list> |
877 */
878 case IO_STMT8:
879 (void)misc_io_checks("WRITE");
880 kwd_errchk(BT_WRITE);
881 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(4));
882 external_io = !intern;
883 goto io_items;
884 /*
885 * <IO stmt> ::= <write> PRINT <print spec> |
886 */
887 case IO_STMT9:
888 (void)misc_io_checks("PRINT");
889 kwd_errchk(BT_PRINT);
890 external_io = !intern;
891 goto io_end;
892 /*
893 * <IO stmt> ::= <write> PRINT <print spec> , <output list> |
894 */
895 case IO_STMT10:
896 (void)misc_io_checks("PRINT");
897 kwd_errchk(BT_PRINT);
898 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(5));
899 external_io = !intern;
900 goto io_items;
901 /*
902 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> READ <io spec> <input list> |
903 */
904 case IO_STMT11:
905 (void)misc_io_checks("READ");
906 kwd_errchk(BT_READ);
907 chk_iospec();
908 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(4));
909 external_io = !intern;
910 nondevice_io = TRUE;
911 goto io_items;
912 /*
913 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> READ <read spec2> |
914 */
915 case IO_STMT12:
916 (void)misc_io_checks("READ");
917 kwd_errchk(BT_READ);
918 external_io = !intern;
919 nondevice_io = TRUE;
920 goto io_end;
921 /*
922 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> READ <read spec3> , <input list> |
923 */
924 case IO_STMT13:
925 (void)misc_io_checks("READ");
926 kwd_errchk(BT_READ);
927 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(5));
928 external_io = !intern;
929 nondevice_io = TRUE;
930 goto io_items;
931 /*
932 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> ACCEPT <read spec4> |
933 */
934 case IO_STMT14:
935 (void)misc_io_checks("ACCEPT");
936 iomsg_check();
937 kwd_errchk(BT_ACCEPT);
938 external_io = !intern;
939 nondevice_io = TRUE;
940 goto io_end;
941 /*
942 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> ACCEPT <read spec3> , <input list> |
943 */
944 case IO_STMT15:
945 (void)misc_io_checks("ACCEPT");
946 iomsg_check();
947 kwd_errchk(BT_ACCEPT);
948 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(5));
949 external_io = !intern;
950 nondevice_io = TRUE;
951 goto io_items;
952 /*
953 * <IO stmt> ::= <write> ENCODE <encode spec> <optional comma> <output
954 *list> |
955 */
956 case IO_STMT16:
957 (void)misc_io_checks("ENCODE");
958 iomsg_check();
959 kwd_errchk(BT_ENCODE);
960 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(5));
961 external_io = FALSE;
962 nondevice_io = TRUE;
963 goto io_items;
964 /*
965 * <IO stmt> ::= <write> ENCODE <encode spec> |
966 */
967 case IO_STMT17:
968 (void)misc_io_checks("ENCODE");
969 iomsg_check();
970 kwd_errchk(BT_ENCODE);
971 external_io = FALSE;
972 nondevice_io = TRUE;
973 goto io_end;
974 /*
975 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> DECODE <encode spec> <optional comma> <input list>
976 */
977 case IO_STMT18:
978 (void)misc_io_checks("DECODE");
979 iomsg_check();
980 kwd_errchk(BT_DECODE);
981 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(5));
982 external_io = FALSE;
983 nondevice_io = TRUE;
984 goto io_items;
985 /*
986 * <IO stmt> ::= <read> DECODE <encode spec> |
987 */
988 case IO_STMT19:
989 (void)misc_io_checks("DECODE");
990 iomsg_check();
991 kwd_errchk(BT_DECODE);
992 external_io = FALSE;
993 nondevice_io = TRUE;
994 goto io_end;
995
996 io_items:
997 if (fmttyp == FT_NML) {
998 IOERR(212);
999 break;
1000 }
1001 count = 4;
1002 rtlRtn = getBasicScalarRWRtn(is_read, fmttyp);
1003 iofunc = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, is_read ? 0 : INTENT_IN);
1004 SEQUENTP(iofunc, 1); /* TPR1786 */
1005
1006 for (; iolptr; iolptr = iolptr->next) {
1007 switch (iolptr->id) {
1008 case IE_OPTDO:
1009 stkptr = iolptr->element;
1010 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
1011 doinfo = iolptr->doinfo;
1012 /* TBD:
1013 I would rather call a function to compute the lastvalue:
1014 index_var = f90_lastval(m1, m2, m3)
1015 */
1016 /*
1017 * Compute last value of index variable:
1018 * index_var = max( (m2 - m1 + m3)/m3, 0)
1019 */
1020 gen_lastval(doinfo);
1021 goto array_io_item;
1022 case IE_EXPR:
1023 stkptr = iolptr->element;
1024 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
1025 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
1026 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
1027 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_IDENT && AD_ASSUMSZ(ad)) {
1028 /* illegal use of assumed size array */
1029 ast2 = astb.i0;
1030 IOERR(215);
1031 }
1032 goto array_io_item;
1033 }
1034 /* does this have a shape */
1035 if (SST_SHAPEG(stkptr))
1036 goto array_io_item;
1037
1038 /* at this point, io item is a scalar */
1039
1040 if (dtype == DT_HOLL) {
1041 /* semantic stack type is hollerith, but want its associated
1042 * character constant.
1043 */
1044 sptr1 = CONVAL1G(SST_SYMG(stkptr));
1045 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr1);
1046#if DEBUG
1047 assert(DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR, "io_item: HOLL not char", sptr1, 3);
1048#endif
1049 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype);
1050 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_cnst(sptr1));
1051 }
1052 ast2 = astb.i1;
1053 ast3 = astb.i0;
1054 (void)mkarg(stkptr, &dum);
1055 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1056 if (is_read) {
1057 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID) {
1058 DOCHK(A_SPTRG(ast));
1059 }
1060 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_IDENT || SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_DERIVED)
1061 set_assn(sym_of_ast(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1062 else if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_LVALUE)
1063 set_assn(sym_of_ast(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1064 }
1065 if (!DT_ISBASIC(dtype) && SST_IDG(stkptr) != S_DERIVED) {
1066 int bytfunc;
1067 int udt;
1068
1069 FtnRtlEnum aggrRWRtn = getAggrRWRtn(is_read);
1070
1071 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_IDENT) {
1072 sptr = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
1073 udt = DTYPEG(sptr);
1074 } else if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_EXPR) {
1075 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID) {
1076 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
1077 udt = DTYPEG(sptr);
1078 } else {
1079 sptr = 0;
1080 udt = A_DTYPEG(ast);
1081 }
1082 } else {
1083 sptr = SST_LSYMG(stkptr);
1084 udt = DTYPEG(sptr);
1085 }
1086 if (DTYG(udt) == TY_DERIVED) {
1087 int iotype_ast = 0, vlist_ast = 0;
1088 int fsptr, argcnt, has_io, asn, tast;
1089 const char *iotype;
1090 ITEM *arglist;
1091
1092 dtype = udt;
1093 has_io = dtype_has_defined_io(dtype);
1094#if DEBUG
1095 assert(has_io, "unknown status from dtype_has_defined_io()", 0, 3);
1096#endif
1097 if (has_io & functype[is_read][fmttyp]) {
1098 if (fmttyp == FT_UNFORMATTED) {
1099 argcnt = 4;
1100 } else {
1101 int tast;
1102 argcnt = 6;
1103 if (fmttyp == FT_NML) {
1104 iotype = "NAMELIST";
1105 vlist_ast = astb.i0;
1106 iotype_ast = mk_cnst(getstring(iotype, strlen(iotype)));
1107 } else if (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) {
1108 iotype = "LISTDIRECTED";
1109 vlist_ast = astb.i0;
1110 iotype_ast = mk_cnst(getstring(iotype, strlen(iotype)));
1111 } else {
1112 asn = gen_dtsfmt_args(&iotype_ast, &vlist_ast);
1113 asn = call_dtsfmt(iotype_ast, vlist_ast);
1114 tast = add_cgoto(asn);
1115 }
1116 }
1117 arglist = gen_dtio_args(stkptr, ast, iotype_ast, vlist_ast);
1118
1119 fsptr = resolve_defined_io((is_read ? 0 : 1), stkptr, arglist);
1120 if (!fsptr) {
1121 /*unable to find io routine*/
1122 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno,
1123 "- Unable to resolve user defined io ", CNULL);
1124
1125 } else {
1126 /* set the upper bound of descriptor here? */
1127 ast = get_defined_io_call(fsptr, argcnt, arglist);
1128 (void)add_stmt(ast);
1129 /* error handling in parent in case of error */
1130 if (argcnt == 4) {
1131 tast = (arglist->next->next)->ast;
1132 } else {
1133 tast = (arglist->next->next->next->next)->ast;
1134 }
1135 sptr1 = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_dts_stat, DT_NONE, 0);
1136 ast1 = begin_io_call(A_CALL, sptr1, 1);
1137 (void)add_io_arg(mk_unop(OP_VAL, tast, DT_INT4));
1138 (void)add_stmt(ast1);
1139 (void)add_cgoto(tast);
1140 }
1141 break;
1142 } else {
1143 gen_derived_io(sptr, aggrRWRtn, is_read);
1144 }
1145 } else {
1146 bytfunc = mk_iofunc(aggrRWRtn, DT_INT, is_read ? 0 : INTENT_IN);
1147 if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
1148 /* just transfer a stream of n bytes */
1149 i = mk_isz_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT8);
1150 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, bytfunc, 4);
1151 (void)add_io_arg(i); /* length, stride */
1152 (void)add_io_arg(astb.i0);
1153 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1154 (void)add_io_arg(astb.k1); /* explicit item_length */
1155 } else {
1156 i = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT8);
1157 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, bytfunc, 4);
1158 (void)add_io_arg(ast2); /* length, stride */
1159 (void)add_io_arg(ast3);
1160 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1161 (void)add_io_arg(i); /* explicit item_length */
1162 }
1163 }
1164 } else if (fmttyp != FT_UNFORMATTED && !is_read &&
1165 (dtype == DT_INT8 || dtype == DT_INT4 || dtype == DT_SINT ||
1166 dtype == DT_BINT || dtype == DT_LOG8 || dtype == DT_LOG ||
1167 dtype == DT_SLOG || dtype == DT_BLOG || dtype == DT_REAL4 ||
1168 dtype == DT_REAL8 || dtype == DT_QUAD || dtype == DT_CMPLX8 ||
1169 dtype == DT_CMPLX16 ||
1170#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
1171 dtype == DT_QCMPLX ||
1172#endif
1173 (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR && fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED))) {
1174
1175 i = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(getWriteByDtypeRtn(dtype, fmttyp)),
1176 DT_INT);
1177 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_CHAR) {
1178 ast = mk_unop(OP_VAL, ast, dtype);
1179 }
1180 ast1 = mk_cval((INT)dtype_to_arg(dtype), DT_INT4);
1181 ast1 = mk_unop(OP_VAL, ast1, DT_INT4);
1182 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, i, 2);
1183 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1184 (void)add_io_arg(ast1); /* type */
1185 } else {
1186 ast1 = mk_cval((INT)dtype_to_arg(dtype), DT_INT);
1187 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, iofunc, 4);
1188 (void)add_io_arg(ast1); /* type, length, stride */
1189 (void)add_io_arg(ast2);
1190 (void)add_io_arg(ast3);
1191 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1192 }
1193 ast = end_io_call();
1194 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
1195 break;
1196
1197 case IE_DOBEGIN:
1198 doinfo = iolptr->doinfo;
1199 ast = do_begin(doinfo);
1200 {
1201 /* for any stds attached to this DO, add them after
1202 * the DO begin; these STDs are simply linked in by
1203 * altering the NEXT & PREV fields of the DO's std
1204 * and the first and last stds. in the list.
1205 */
1206 int s, s1;
1207 s1 = add_stmt_after(ast, (int)STD_PREV(0));
1208 s = iolptr->l_std;
1209 if (s) {
1210 STD_NEXT(s1) = s;
1211 STD_PREV(s) = s1;
1212 s1 = s;
1213 /* find last STD in the list attached to the DO */
1214 while (STD_NEXT(s1))
1215 s1 = STD_NEXT(s1);
1216 STD_PREV(0) = s1;
1217 }
1218 }
1219 NEED_DOIF(i, DI_DO);
1220 break;
1221
1222 case IE_DOEND:
1223 do_end(iolptr->doinfo);
1224 break;
1225
1226 default:
1227 interr("io_items, badIE", iolptr->id, 3);
1228 }
1229
1230 continue;
1231
1232 array_io_item:
1233 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
1234 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
1235 if (no_data_components(dtype))
1236 continue;
1237 if (!((SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_EXPR && DTYG(dtype) == TY_DERIVED)))
1238 (void)mkarg(stkptr, &dum);
1239 if (is_read) {
1240 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_IDENT)
1241 set_assn(sym_of_ast(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1242 else if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_LVALUE)
1243 set_assn(sym_of_ast(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1244 }
1245 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1246 needDescr = need_descriptor_ast(ast);
1247 rtlRtn = getArrayRWRtn(is_read, fmttyp, dtype, !needDescr);
1248 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
1249 if (!needDescr) {
1250 /* collapse a read/write of an array into a single call
1251 * which doesn't require a descriptor
1252 */
1253 if (dtype != DT_ASSCHAR && dtype != DT_DEFERCHAR) {
1254 ast3 = SST_CVLENG(stkptr);
1255 if (!ast3)
1256 ast3 = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1257 } else {
1258 ast3 = string_expr_length(ast);
1259 }
1260 rw_array(ast, ast3, dtype, rtlRtn);
1261 goto end_io_item;
1262 }
1263 ast1 = mk_cval((INT)ty_to_lib[TY_CHAR], DT_INT);
1264 ast2 = astb.i1; /* tpr 1786: this gets elementalized later */
1265 if (dtype != DT_ASSCHAR && dtype != DT_DEFERCHAR) {
1266 ast3 = SST_CVLENG(stkptr);
1267 if (!ast3)
1268 ast3 = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1269 } else {
1270 ast3 = string_expr_length(ast);
1271 }
1272 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, iofunc, 4);
1273 (void)add_io_arg(ast1); /* type, length, stride */
1274 (void)add_io_arg(ast2);
1275 (void)add_io_arg(ast3);
1276 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1277 }
1278 else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
1279 ast1 = mk_cval((INT)ty_to_lib[TY_NCHAR], DT_INT);
1280 ast2 = astb.i1; /* tpr 1786: this gets elementalized later */
1281 if (dtype != DT_ASSNCHAR && dtype != DT_DEFERNCHAR)
1282 ast3 = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1283 else {
1284 i = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_nlena), DT_INT);
1285 ast3 = begin_call(A_FUNC, i, 1);
1286 add_arg(ast);
1287 }
1288 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, iofunc, 4);
1289 (void)add_io_arg(ast1); /* type, length, stride */
1290 (void)add_io_arg(ast2);
1291 (void)add_io_arg(ast3);
1292 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1293 }
1294 else if (!DT_ISBASIC(dtype)) {
1295 int bytfunc;
1296 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED &&
1297 (dtype_has_defined_io(dtype) & functype[is_read][fmttyp])) {
1298 const char *iotype;
1299 int tast, iotype_ast = 0, vlist_ast = 0, argcnt, asn, fsptr;
1300 int shape, forall, triplet_list, n, lb, ub, st, newast;
1301 int index_var, triplet, dovar, list, sym, triple;
1302 ITEM *arglist;
1303 int subs[7], std;
1304 int i;
1305 if (fmttyp == FT_UNFORMATTED) {
1306 argcnt = 4;
1307 } else {
1308 argcnt = 6;
1309 if (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) {
1310 iotype = "LISTDIRECTED";
1311 vlist_ast = astb.i0;
1312 iotype_ast = mk_cnst(getstring(iotype, strlen(iotype)));
1313 } else if (fmttyp != FT_NML) {
1314 /* only generates the argument, no call */
1315 asn = gen_dtsfmt_args(&iotype_ast, &vlist_ast);
1316 }
1317 }
1318 /* need to make a loop here */
1319
1320 arglist = gen_dtio_args(stkptr, ast, iotype_ast, vlist_ast);
1321 shape = A_SHAPEG(arglist->ast);
1322
1323 /* make forall */
1324 start_astli();
1325 numdim = SHD_NDIM(shape);
1326 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
1327 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
1328 subs[i] = ASD_SUBS(A_ASDG(ast1), i);
1329 }
1330 for (i = numdim - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
1331 /* make each forall index */
1332 lb = check_member(ast1, SHD_LWB(shape, i));
1333 ub = check_member(ast1, SHD_UPB(shape, i));
1334 st = check_member(ast1, SHD_STRIDE(shape, i));
1335 if (A_DTYPEG(lb) == DT_INT8 || A_DTYPEG(ub) == DT_INT8 ||
1336 A_DTYPEG(st) == DT_INT8)
1337 dtype = DT_INT8;
1338 else
1339 dtype = astb.bnd.dtype;
1340 if (A_DTYPEG(lb) == DT_INT8 || A_DTYPEG(ub) == DT_INT8 ||
1341 A_DTYPEG(st) == DT_INT8)
1342 sym = sym_get_scalar("i", 0, DT_INT8);
1343 else
1344 sym = sym_get_scalar("i", 0, DT_INT);
1345 list = add_astli();
1346 triple = mk_triple(lb, ub, st);
1347 ASTLI_SPTR(list) = sym;
1348 ASTLI_TRIPLE(list) = triple;
1349 subs[i] = mk_id(sym);
1350 }
1351 forall = mk_stmt(A_FORALL, 0);
1352 A_LISTP(forall, ASTLI_HEAD);
1353 A_IFEXPRP(forall, 0);
1354
1355 n = 0;
1356 triplet_list = A_LISTG(forall);
1357 for (; triplet_list; triplet_list = ASTLI_NEXT(triplet_list)) {
1358 n++;
1359 newast = mk_stmt(A_DO, 0);
1360 index_var = ASTLI_SPTR(triplet_list);
1361 triplet = ASTLI_TRIPLE(triplet_list);
1362 dovar = mk_id(index_var);
1363 lb = A_LBDG(triplet);
1364 ub = A_UPBDG(triplet);
1365 st = A_STRIDEG(triplet);
1366 A_M1P(newast, lb);
1367 A_M2P(newast, ub);
1368 A_M3P(newast, st);
1369 A_M4P(newast, 0);
1370 A_DOVARP(newast, dovar);
1371
1372 std = add_stmt(newast);
1373 }
1374 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR)
1375 ast1 = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(ast), subs, numdim, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast)));
1376 else
1377 ast1 = mk_subscr(ast, subs, numdim, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast)));
1378
1379 /* need to generate a new stkptr */
1380 arglist->t.stkp = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
1381 SST_ASTP(arglist->t.stkp, ast1);
1382 SST_DTYPEP(arglist->t.stkp, A_DTYPEG(ast1));
1383 SST_SHAPEP(arglist->t.stkp, 0);
1384 arglist->ast = ast1;
1385 SST_IDP(arglist->t.stkp, S_EXPR);
1386 mkexpr(arglist->t.stkp);
1387 fsptr =
1388 resolve_defined_io((is_read ? 0 : 1), arglist->t.stkp, arglist);
1389 if (!fsptr) {
1390 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "- Unable to resolve user defined io",
1391 CNULL);
1392 } else {
1393 /* need to make a loop */
1394 if (fmttyp != FT_UNFORMATTED && fmttyp != FT_LIST_DIRECTED &&
1395 fmttyp != FT_NML) {
1396 asn = call_dtsfmt(iotype_ast, vlist_ast);
1397 tast = add_cgoto(asn);
1398 }
1399 tast = get_defined_io_call(fsptr, argcnt, arglist);
1400 (void)add_stmt_after(tast, std);
1401 if (argcnt == 4) {
1402 tast = (arglist->next->next)->ast;
1403 } else {
1404 tast = (arglist->next->next->next->next)->ast;
1405 }
1406 asn = mk_assn_stmt(ast_ioret(), tast, DT_INT);
1407 (void)add_stmt(asn);
1408 tast = add_cgoto(asn);
1409 }
1410 triplet_list = A_LISTG(forall);
1411 for (; triplet_list; triplet_list = ASTLI_NEXT(triplet_list)) {
1412 newast = mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0);
1413 (void)add_stmt(newast);
1414 }
1415
1416 continue;
1417 } else {
1418 bytfunc =
1419 mk_iofunc(getAggrRWRtn(is_read), DT_INT, is_read ? 0 : INTENT_IN);
1420 ast2 = AD_NUMELM(AD_DPTR(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)));
1421 if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
1422 /* just transfer a stream of n bytes */
1423 ast3 = mk_isz_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT8);
1424 ast2 = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ast2, ast3, DT_INT8);
1425 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, bytfunc, 4);
1426 (void)add_io_arg(ast2); /* length, stride */
1427 (void)add_io_arg(astb.i0);
1428 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1429 (void)add_io_arg(astb.k1); /* explicit item_length */
1430 } else {
1431 ast3 = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT8);
1432 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, bytfunc, 4);
1433 (void)add_io_arg(ast2); /* length, stride */
1434 (void)add_io_arg(ast3);
1435 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item */
1436 (void)add_io_arg(ast3); /* explicit item_length */
1437 }
1438 }
1439 } else {
1440 if (!need_descriptor_ast(ast)) {
1441 /* collapse a read/write of an array into a single call
1442 * which doesn't require a descriptor
1443 */
1444 ast3 = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1445 rw_array(ast, ast3, dtype, rtlRtn);
1446 goto end_io_item;
1447 }
1448 (void)begin_io_call(
1449 A_FUNC, mk_hpfiofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, is_read ? 0 : INTENT_IN), 1);
1450 (void)add_io_arg(ast); /* item only */
1451 }
1452 end_io_item:
1453 ast = end_io_call();
1454 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
1455 }
1456
1457 io_end:
1458 if (fmttyp == FT_NML) {
1459 if (is_read)
1460 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_nmlr;
1461 else
1462 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_nmlw;
1463 sptr = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, is_read ? 0 : INTENT_IN);
1464 /*
1465 * First, create and "address" of the descriptor for the
1466 * namelist group; then, call the appropriate routine
1467 */
1468 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 1);
1469 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_NML));
1470 ast = end_io_call();
1471 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
1472 if (is_read)
1473 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_nmlr_end;
1474 else
1475 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_nmlw_end;
1476 sptr = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, 0);
1477 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 0);
1478 ast = end_io_call();
1479 } else {
1480 if (fmttyp == FT_UNFORMATTED)
1481 rtlRtn = unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_SWAPPED_IO_IDX].end;
1482 else if (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) {
1483 if (is_read)
1484 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_ldr_end;
1485 else
1486 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_ldw_end;
1487 } else {
1488 if (is_read)
1489 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_fmtr_end;
1490 else
1491 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_fmtw_end;
1492 }
1493 sptr = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, 0);
1494 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 0);
1495 ast = end_io_call();
1496 }
1497 if (intern_tmp) {
1498 copy_back_to_replic_sect(intern_array, intern_tmp);
1499 intern_tmp = 0;
1500 }
1501 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
1502 goto end_IO_STMT;
1503 /*
1504 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> INQUIRE <iolp> IOLENGTH = <var ref> ) <output
1505 *list> |
1506 */
1507 case IO_STMT20:
1508 (void)misc_io_checks("INQUIRE");
1509 iomsg_check();
1510 chk_var(RHS(6), PT_IOLENGTH, DT_INT);
1511 iolptr = (IOL *)SST_BEGG(RHS(8));
1512 ast = astb.i0;
1513 ast = mk_assn_stmt(PTV(PT_IOLENGTH), ast, DT_INT);
1514 (void)add_stmt_after(ast, (int)STD_PREV(0));
1515 for (; iolptr; iolptr = iolptr->next) {
1516 switch (iolptr->id) {
1517 case IE_OPTDO:
1518 stkptr = iolptr->element;
1519 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
1520 doinfo = iolptr->doinfo;
1521 /* TBD:
1522 I would rather call a function to compute the lastvalue:
1523 index_var = f90_lastval(m1, m2, m3)
1524 */
1525 /*
1526 * Compute last value of index variable:
1527 * index_var = max( (m2 - m1 + m3)/m3, 0)
1528 */
1529 gen_lastval(doinfo);
1530 goto array_iol;
1531 case IE_EXPR:
1532 stkptr = iolptr->element;
1533 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
1534 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
1535 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
1536 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_IDENT && AD_ASSUMSZ(ad)) {
1537 /* illegal use of assumed array */
1538 ast2 = astb.i0;
1539 IOERR(215);
1540 }
1541 goto array_iol;
1542 }
1543
1544 /* at this point, io item is a scalar */
1545
1546 nelems = astb.i1;
1547 goto accum_it;
1548
1549 case IE_DOBEGIN:
1550 doinfo = iolptr->doinfo;
1551 ast = do_begin(doinfo);
1552 {
1553 /* for any stds attached to this DO, add them after
1554 * the DO begin; these STDs are simply linked in by
1555 * altering the NEXT & PREV fields of the DO's std
1556 * and the first and last stds. in the list.
1557 */
1558 int s, s1;
1559 s1 = add_stmt_after(ast, (int)STD_PREV(0));
1560 s = iolptr->l_std;
1561 if (s) {
1562 STD_NEXT(s1) = s;
1563 STD_PREV(s) = s1;
1564 s1 = s;
1565 /* find last STD in the list attached to the DO */
1566 while (STD_NEXT(s1))
1567 s1 = STD_NEXT(s1);
1568 STD_PREV(0) = s1;
1569 }
1570 }
1571 NEED_DOIF(i, DI_DO);
1572 break;
1573
1574 case IE_DOEND:
1575 do_end(iolptr->doinfo);
1576 break;
1577
1578 default:
1579 interr("iol_items, badIE", iolptr->id, 3);
1580 }
1581
1582 continue;
1583
1584 array_iol:
1585 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
1586 (void)mkarg(stkptr, &dum);
1587 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1588 nelems = size_of_ast(ast);
1589
1590 accum_it:
1591 if (dtype == DT_HOLL) {
1592 /* semantic stack type is hollerith, but want its associated
1593 * character constant.
1594 */
1595 sptr1 = CONVAL1G(SST_SYMG(stkptr));
1596 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr1);
1597#if DEBUG
1598 assert(DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR, "io_item: HOLL not char", sptr1, 3);
1599#endif
1600 ast = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1601 } else if (!DT_ISBASIC(dtype))
1602 /* treat aggr. as byte stream */
1603 ast = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1604 else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
1605 (void)mkarg(stkptr, &dum);
1606 ast2 = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1607 i = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_lena), DT_INT);
1608 ast = begin_call(A_FUNC, i, 1);
1609 add_arg(ast2);
1610 }
1611 else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
1612 (void)mkarg(stkptr, &dum);
1613 ast2 = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1614 i = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_nlena), DT_INT);
1615 ast = begin_call(A_FUNC, i, 1);
1616 add_arg(ast2);
1617 ast1 = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1618 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ast, ast1, DT_INT);
1619 }
1620 else
1621 ast = mk_cval(size_of(dtype), DT_INT);
1622
1623 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ast, nelems, DT_INT);
1624 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, PTV(PT_IOLENGTH), ast, DT_INT);
1625 ast = mk_assn_stmt(PTV(PT_IOLENGTH), ast, DT_INT);
1626 (void)add_stmt_after(ast, (int)STD_PREV(0));
1627 }
1628 external_io = TRUE;
1629 nondevice_io = TRUE;
1630 goto end_IO_STMT;
1631
1632 /*
1633 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> WAIT <iolp> <spec list> ) |
1634 */
1635 case IO_STMT21:
1636 (void)misc_io_checks("WAIT");
1637 iomsg_check();
1638 UNIT_CHECK;
1639 kwd_errchk(BT_WAIT);
1640 PT_CHECK(PT_ID, astb.ptr0);
1641 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_wait, DT_INT, 0);
1642 fix_iostat();
1643 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 4);
1644 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_UNIT));
1645 (void)add_io_arg(mk_cval(bitv, DT_INT));
1646 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_IOSTAT));
1647 (void)add_io_arg(PTARG(PT_ID));
1648 ast = end_io_call();
1649 ast = add_cgoto(ast);
1650 external_io = TRUE;
1651 nondevice_io = TRUE;
1652 goto end_IO_STMT;
1653 /*
1654 * <IO stmt> ::= <null> FLUSH <unit info>
1655 */
1656 case IO_STMT22:
1657 (void)misc_io_checks("FLUSH");
1658 iomsg_check();
1659 kwd_errchk(BT_FLUSH);
1660 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_flush;
1661 goto rewind_shared;
1662
1663 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
1664 /*
1665 * <unit info> ::= <unit id> |
1666 */
1667 case UNIT_INFO1:
1668 noparens = TRUE;
1669 break;
1670 /*
1671 * <unit info> ::= <iolp> <unit data list> )
1672 */
1673 case UNIT_INFO2:
1674 break;
1675
1676 /*
1677 * <unit info> ::= <iolp> <unit id> )
1678 */
1679 case UNIT_INFO3:
1680 break;
1681
1682 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
1683 /*
1684 * <unit data list> ::= <unit data list> , <unit data> |
1685 */
1686 case UNIT_DATA_LIST1:
1687 break;
1688 /*
1689 * <unit data list> ::= <unit id> , <unit data> |
1690 */
1691 case UNIT_DATA_LIST2:
1692 break;
1693 /*
1694 * <unit data list> ::= <unit data>
1695 */
1696 case UNIT_DATA_LIST3:
1697 break;
1698
1699 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
1700 /*
1701 * <unit data> ::= UNIT = <unit id> |
1702 */
1703 case UNIT_DATA1:
1704 PT_SET(PT_UNIT);
1705 break;
1706 /*
1707 * <unit data> ::= ERR = <reflabel> |
1708 */
1709 case UNIT_DATA2:
1710 bitv |= BITV_ERR;
1711 PT_SET(PT_ERR);
1712 PTV(PT_ERR) = SST_SYMG(RHS(3)); /* sptr not ast */
1713 nondevice_io = TRUE;
1714 break;
1715 /*
1716 * <unit data> ::= IOSTAT = <var ref> |
1717 */
1718 case UNIT_DATA3:
1719 bitv |= BITV_IOSTAT;
1720 PT_SET(PT_IOSTAT);
1721 chk_var(RHS(3), PT_IOSTAT, DT_INT);
1722 PTV(PT_IOSTAT) = SST_ASTG(RHS(3));
1723 set_assn(sym_of_ast(SST_ASTG(RHS(3))));
1724 nondevice_io = TRUE;
1725 break;
1726 /*
1727 * <unit data> ::= IOMSG = <var ref>
1728 */
1729 case UNIT_DATA4:
1730 bitv |= BITV_IOMSG;
1731 PT_SET(PT_IOMSG);
1732 chk_var(RHS(3), PT_IOMSG, DT_CHAR);
1733 PTV(PT_IOMSG) = SST_ASTG(RHS(3));
1734 nondevice_io = TRUE;
1735 break;
1736
1737 /*
1738 * <unit data> ::= NEWUNIT = <var ref> |
1739 */

1741 if (PTV(PT_UNIT) && !PTS(PT_NEWUNIT)) {

1743 break;
1744 }
1745 PT_SET(PT_NEWUNIT);
1746 chk_var(RHS(3), PT_NEWUNIT, SST_DTYPEG(RHS(3)));
1747 PTV(PT_UNIT) = PTV(PT_NEWUNIT);
1748 PT_VARREF(PT_UNIT, PTVARREF(PT_NEWUNIT));
1749 set_assn(sym_of_ast(SST_ASTG(RHS(3))));
1750 break;

1759 break;

1766 scn.stmtyp != TK_PRINT)

1768 chk_unitid((SST *)NULL);
1769 unit_star = TRUE;
1770 break;

2049 PTV(PT_NML) = mk_id(get_nml_array(sptr));
2050 if (fmttyp != FT_UNFORMATTED) {
2051 if (fmttyp == FT_NML)
2052 IOERR2(202, "NML");
2053 else
2054 IOERR(212);
2055 }

2057 nml_group = sptr;
2058 REFP(sptr, 1); /* ref ==> must be initialized */
2059 for (i = CMEMFG(sptr); i; i = NML_NEXT(i)) {
2060 sptr = NML_SPTR(i);
2061 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_NONE)
2062 sem_set_storage_class(sptr);
2063 }
2064 break;
2065 /*
2066 * <spec item> ::= <expression> |
2067 */
2068 case SPEC_ITEM31:
2069 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2070 if (SST_IDG(RHS(1)) == S_IDENT) {
2071 if (STYPEG(SST_SYMG(RHS(1))) == ST_NML) {
2072 sptr = refsym(SST_SYMG(RHS(1)), OC_OTHER);
2073 goto nml_io;
2074 }
2075 }
2076 if (!PTV(PT_UNIT))
2077 chk_unitid(RHS(1));
2078 else
2079 chk_fmtid(RHS(1));
2080 break;
2081 /*
2082 * <spec item> ::= * |
2083 */
2084 case SPEC_ITEM32:
2085 if (scn.stmtyp != TK_READ && scn.stmtyp != TK_WRITE &&
2086 scn.stmtyp != TK_PRINT)
2087 IOERR2(201, "UNIT=*");
2088 if (PTV(PT_UNIT))
2089 chk_fmtid((SST *)NULL);
2090 else {
2091 chk_unitid((SST *)NULL);
2092 unit_star = TRUE;
2093 }
2094 break;

2097 */

2100 error(1050, ERR_Severe, gbl.lineno,
2101 "I/O statement ADVANCE specifier in", CNULL);
2102 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2103 PT_SET(PT_ADVANCE);
2104 bitv |= BITV_ADVANCE;
2105 chk_expr(RHS(3), PT_ADVANCE, DT_CHAR);
2106 break;

2113 PT_SET(PT_EOR);

2115 break;

2155 goto inq_var_or_expr_spec;

2160 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2161 PT_SET(PT_SIZE);
2162 bitv |= BITV_SIZE;
2163 gen_spec_item_tmp(RHS(3), PT_SIZE, DT_INT8);
2164 break;
2165 /*
2166 * <spec item> ::= ASYNCHRONOUS = <expression> |
2167 */
2168 case SPEC_ITEM41:
2169 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2170 i = PT_ASYNCHRONOUS;
2171 dtype = DT_CHAR;
2172 goto inq_var_or_expr_spec;

2178 i = PT_DECIMAL;
2179 dtype = DT_CHAR;
2180 rw03 = TRUE;
2181 open03 = TRUE;

2186 case SPEC_ITEM43:
2187 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2188 i = PT_ENCODING;
2189 dtype = DT_CHAR;
2190 rw03 = TRUE;
2191 open03 = TRUE;

2193 break;

2198 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2199 i = PT_SIGN;
2200 dtype = DT_CHAR;
2201 open03 = TRUE;
2202 rw03 = TRUE;
2203 goto inq_var_or_expr_spec;
2204 /*

2206 */

2208 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2209 PT_SET(PT_STREAM);
2210 chk_var(RHS(3), PT_STREAM, DT_CHAR);
2211 break;
2212 /*
2213 * <spec item> ::= ROUND = <expression>
2214 */
2215 case SPEC_ITEM46:
2216 nondevice_io = TRUE;
2217 i = PT_ROUND;
2218 dtype = DT_CHAR;
2219 open03 = TRUE;
2220 rw03 = TRUE;
2221 /* fall thru */
2222 inq_var_or_expr_spec:
2223 PT_SET(i);
2224 if (scn.stmtyp == TK_INQUIRE)
2225 chk_var(RHS(3), i, dtype);
2226 else
2227 chk_expr(RHS(3), i, dtype);
2228 break;
2229
