4933
4934/* create the array (ST_PLIST) representing the format; name is
4935 * derived from its label
4936 */
4937static int
4938get_fmt_array(int lab, int stype)
4939{
4940 char *nm, *p;
4941 char name[12]; /* z__fmtddddd */
4942 int sptr;
4943
4944 nm = SYMNAME(lab);
4945 nm += 2; /* skip past .L */
4946 while (*nm == '0')
4947 nm++; /* skip over leading 0's */
4948 strcpy(name, "z__fmt");
4949 p = name + 6;
4950 while ((*p++ = *nm++))
4951 ;
4952 sptr = getsymbol(name);
4953 if (stype == ST_PLIST) {
4954 STYPEP(sptr, ST_PLIST);
4955 /* there may have been a format statement from the outer procedure with
4956 * the same label. If this is an internal procedure, make a new symbol
4957 */
4958 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr) && INTERNALG(lab)) {
4959 sptr = insert_sym(sptr);
4960 STYPEP(sptr, ST_PLIST);
4961 }
4962 if (gbl.internal <= 1 || INTERNALG(lab))
4963 SCOPEP(sptr, stb.curr_scope);
4964 if (gbl.internal > 1) {
4965 if (INTERNALG(lab))
4966 INTERNALP(sptr, 1);
4967 else
4968 INTERNREFP(sptr, 1);
4969 }
4970 if (sem.parallel || sem.orph || sem.target || sem.teams) {
4971 set_parref_flag(sptr, sptr, BLK_UPLEVEL_SPTR(sem.scope_level));
4972 PARREFP(sptr, 1);
4973 }
4974 } else {
4975 sptr = declsym_newscope(sptr, stype, 0);
4976 if (gbl.internal > 1) {
4977 INTERNALP(sptr, 1);
4978 }
4979 ASSNP(sptr, 1);
4980 HCCSYMP(sptr, 1);
4981 }
4982 return sptr;
4983}
4984
4985/** \brief Create the array (ST_PLIST) representing the namelist.
4986 *
4987 * The name is derived from the namelist group name.
4988 */
4989int
4990get_nml_array(int nml)
4991{
4992 int sptr;
4993
4994 if (ADDRESSG(nml))
4995 return ADDRESSG(nml);
4996 sptr = get_next_sym(SYMNAME(nml), "nml");
4997 STYPEP(sptr, ST_PLIST);
4998 CCSYMP(sptr, 1);
4999 SCP(sptr, SC_STATIC);
5000 DTYPEP(sptr, DT_PTR);
5001 ADDRESSP(nml, sptr);
5002 /* plist will be init'd only if the namelist variable
5003 * is referenced.
5004 */
5005 return sptr;
5006}
5007
5008static int
5009ast_ioret(void)
5010{
5011 static int ast;
5012 int sptr;
5013
5014 if (io_sc != SC_PRIVATE) {
5015 sptr = getsymbol("z__io");
5016 sptr = declsym_newscope(sptr, ST_VAR, DT_INT);
5017 /*
5018 * Some test suitable for deciding the variable is already created.
5019 if (!SCG(sptr)) {
5020 */
5021 SCP(sptr, io_sc);
5022 ast = mk_id(sptr); /* note that ast is static */
5023 ASSNP(sptr, 1);
5024 HCCSYMP(sptr, 1);
5025/*
5026}
5027 */
5028 } else {
5029 sptr = getsymbol("z__io_p");
5030 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_UNKNOWN) {
5031 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
5032 DTYPEP(sptr, DT_INT);
5033 DCLDP(sptr, 1);
5034 SCP(sptr, io_sc);
5035 SCOPEP(sptr, stb.curr_scope);
5036 ASSNP(sptr, 1);
5037 HCCSYMP(sptr, 1);
5038 }
5039 ast = mk_id(sptr);
5040 }
5041
5042 return ast;
5043}
5044
5045/* ast_type - A_FUNC or A_CALL */
5046/* count - number of arguments */
5047/* func - sptr of function to invoke */
5048static int
5049begin_io_call(int ast_type, int func, int count)
5050{
5051 io_call.ast = begin_call(ast_type, func, count);
5052 io_call.ast_type = ast_type;
5053 return io_call.ast;
5054}
5055
5056/* arg - ast of argument to add */
5057static void
5058add_io_arg(int arg)
5059{
5060 add_arg(arg);
5061}
5062
5063/*
5064 * complete the call to the io support routine. if the function returns
5065 * a value (ast_type is A_FUNC), first generate an assignment of the
5066 * function to a temporary; then, add this statement to the STD list.
5067 * If the function invocation is a call, then just add the call to the
5068 * STD list.
5069 */
5070static int
5071end_io_call(void)
5072{
5073 int asn;
5074 int i;
5075
5076 if (io_call.ast_type == A_FUNC)
5077 asn = mk_assn_stmt(ast_ioret(), io_call.ast, DT_INT);
5078 else
5079 asn = io_call.ast;
5080 io_call.std = add_stmt_after(asn, (int)STD_PREV(0));
5081
5082 for (i = 0; i <= PT_MAXV; i++) {
5083 if (i == PT_SIZE) {
5084 continue;
5085 }
5086 if (PTS(i) && PTTMPUSED(i)) {
5087 int aaa;
5088 if (PTVARREF(i) != 1) {
5089 aaa =
5090 mk_assn_stmt(PTVARREF(i), mk_convert(PTV(i), A_DTYPEG(PTVARREF(i))),
5091 A_DTYPEG(PTVARREF(i)));
5092 add_stmt_after(aaa, io_call.std);
5093 }
5094 if (i != PT_SIZE && i != PT_IOSTAT)
5095 PT_TMPUSED(i, 0);
5096 }
5097 }
5098 return asn;
5099}
5100
5101static int
5102mk_iofunc(FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn, int dtype, int intent)
5103{
5104 int sptr;
5105 sptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), dtype);
5106 NODESCP(sptr, 1);
5107#ifdef SDSCSAFEG
5108 SDSCSAFEP(sptr, 1);
5109#endif
5110 INDEPP(sptr, 1);
5111 TYPDP(sptr, 1); /* force external statement */
5112 INTERNALP(sptr, 0); /* these are not internal functions */
5113 if (intent)
5114 INTENTP(sptr, intent);
5115 return sptr;
5116}
5117
5118static int
5119mk_hpfiofunc(FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn, int dtype, int intent)
5120{
5121 int sptr;
5122
5123 sptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), dtype);
5124 PUREP(sptr, 0);
5125 INDEPP(sptr, 1);
5126#ifdef SDSCSAFEG
5127 SDSCSAFEP(sptr, 1);
5128#endif
5129 TYPDP(sptr, 1); /* force external statement */
5130 if (intent)
5131 INTENTP(sptr, intent);
5132 return sptr;
5133}
5134
5135static LOGICAL
5136need_descriptor_ast(int refast)
5137{
5138 /*
5139 * Determine if an array reference, given its ast, requires a descriptor.
5140 */
5141 if (!XBIT(58, 0x800000) && XBIT(58, 0x40) && A_TYPEG(refast) == A_ID) {
5142 /* only performed for f90 whole array references */
5143 int ss = A_SPTRG(refast);
5144 return ss > NOSYM && (ASSUMSHPG(ss) || POINTERG(ss) || ASUMSZG(ss));
5145 }
5146 return TRUE;
5147}
5148
5149static void
5150rw_array(int refast, int stride, int eldtype, FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn)
5151{
5152 /* collapse a read/write of an array into a single call
5153 * which doesn't require a descriptor
5154 */
5155 int syma;
5156 int ast1, ast2;
5157
5158 ast1 = mk_cval((INT)dtype_to_arg(eldtype), DT_INT);
5159 ast2 = size_of_ast(refast);
5160 syma = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, is_read ? 0 : INTENT_IN);
5161 (void)begin_io_call(A_FUNC, syma, 4);
5162 (void)add_io_arg(ast1); /* type, length, stride */
5163 (void)add_io_arg(ast2);
5164 (void)add_io_arg(stride);
5165 (void)add_io_arg(refast); /* item */
5166}
5167
5168/* ------------------------------------------------------------------------ */
5169static IOL *
5170find_end_iollist(IOL *in_iolptr)
5171{
5172 IOL *iolptr;
5173
5174 iolptr = in_iolptr;
5175
5176 if (iolptr == NULL)
5177 return iolptr;
5178
5179 while (iolptr->next != NULL)
5180 iolptr = iolptr->next;
5181
5182 return iolptr;
5183}
5184
5185static IOL *
5186link_iollist(IOL *first, IOL *last)
5187{
5188 IOL *end;
5189
5190 if (first == NULL)
5191 return last;
5192 if (last == NULL)
5193 return first;
5194
5195 end = find_end_iollist(first);
5196 end->next = last;
5197 return first;
5198}
5199
5200static IOL *
5201get_dobegin(int ast1, int ast2, int ast3)
5202{
5203 int sptr, count;
5204 DOINFO *doinfo;
5205 IOL *dobegin;
5206
5207 /* create a DOINFO record using ast1,ast2,ast3.; the index
5208 * variable is a compiler-created temporary .
5209 */
5210 doinfo = get_doinfo(0);
5211 sptr = get_temp(astb.bnd.dtype);
5212 doinfo->index_var = sptr;
5213 doinfo->init_expr = ast1;
5214 doinfo->limit_expr = ast2;
5215 doinfo->step_expr = ast3 ? ast3 : astb.bnd.one;
5216 count = doinfo->limit_expr;
5217 if (doinfo->init_expr != doinfo->step_expr) {
5218 if (doinfo->init_expr != astb.bnd.zero) {
5219 count = mk_binop(OP_SUB, count, doinfo->init_expr, astb.bnd.dtype);
5220 }
5221 count = mk_binop(OP_ADD, count, doinfo->step_expr, astb.bnd.dtype);
5222 }
5223 if (doinfo->step_expr != astb.bnd.one) {
5224 count = mk_binop(OP_DIV, count, doinfo->step_expr, astb.bnd.dtype);
5225 }
5226 doinfo->count = count;
5227 /*
5228 * Create the DOBEGIN IOL for this index.
5229 */
5230 dobegin = (IOL *)getitem(0, sizeof(IOL));
5231 dobegin->id = IE_DOBEGIN;
5232 dobegin->next = NULL;
5233 dobegin->doinfo = doinfo;
5234 dobegin->l_std = 0;
5235
5236 return dobegin;
5237}
5238
5239static IOL *
5240get_doend(DOINFO *doinfo)
5241{
5242 IOL *doend;
5243 /*
5244 * Create the DOEND IOL for this index;
5245 */
5246 doend = (IOL *)getitem(0, sizeof(IOL));
5247 doend->id = IE_DOEND;
5248 doend->next = NULL;
5249 doend->doinfo = doinfo;
5250 doend->l_std = 0;
5251 return doend;
5252}
5253
5254/* we have a one-dimensional expression, replace a vector subscript
5255 * by the indexast */
5256static int
5257replace_vector_subscript(int ast, int indexast)
5258{
5259 int oldl, newl, oldr, newr, nargs, argt, i, changes, argtnew, sptr;
5260 int asd, nsubs, subs[7], lb;
5261 int dtype;
5262
5263 if (ast == 0)
5264 return 0;
5265 dtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
5266 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
5267 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
5268 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5269 /* expressions */
5270 case A_CNST:
5271 case A_CMPLXC:
5272 break;
5273 case A_BINOP:
5274 oldl = A_LOPG(ast);
5275 oldr = A_ROPG(ast);
5276 newl = replace_vector_subscript(oldl, indexast);
5277 newr = replace_vector_subscript(oldr, indexast);
5278 if (newl != oldl || newr != oldr) {
5279 ast = mk_binop(A_OPTYPEG(ast), newl, newr, dtype);
5280 }
5281 break;
5282 case A_UNOP:
5283 oldl = A_LOPG(ast);
5284 newl = replace_vector_subscript(oldl, indexast);
5285 if (newl != oldl) {
5286 ast = mk_unop(A_OPTYPEG(ast), newl, dtype);
5287 }
5288 break;
5289 case A_CONV:
5290 oldl = A_LOPG(ast);
5291 newl = replace_vector_subscript(oldl, indexast);
5292 if (newl != oldl) {
5293 ast = mk_convert(newl, dtype);
5294 }
5295 break;
5296 case A_PAREN:
5297 oldl = A_LOPG(ast);
5298 newl = replace_vector_subscript(oldl, indexast);
5299 if (newl != oldl) {
5300 ast = mk_paren(newl, dtype);
5301 }
5302 break;
5303 case A_SUBSTR:
5304 oldl = A_LOPG(ast);
5305 newl = replace_vector_subscript(oldl, indexast);
5306 if (newl != oldl) {
5307 ast = mk_substr(newl, A_LEFTG(ast), A_RIGHTG(ast), dtype);
5308 }
5309 break;
5310 case A_INTR:
5311 case A_FUNC:
5312 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
5313 argt = A_ARGSG(ast);
5314 argtnew = mk_argt(nargs);
5315 changes = FALSE;
5316 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
5317 ARGT_ARG(argtnew, i) =
5318 replace_vector_subscript(ARGT_ARG(argt, i), indexast);
5319 if (ARGT_ARG(argtnew, i) != ARGT_ARG(argt, i))
5320 changes = TRUE;
5321 }
5322 if (!changes) {
5323 unmk_argt(nargs);
5324 } else {
5325 ast = mk_func_node(A_TYPEG(ast), A_LOPG(ast), nargs, argtnew);
5326 A_DTYPEP(ast, dtype);
5327 }
5328 break;
5329 case A_MEM:
5330 case A_ID:
5331 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM) {
5332 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast));
5333 } else {
5334 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
5335 }
5336 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
5337 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
5338 /* add a subscript here */
5339 if (ADD_NUMDIM(dtype) != 1) {
5340 interr("replace_vector_subscript: >1 dimensional array ",
5341 ADD_NUMDIM(dtype), 3);
5342 }
5343 ast = mk_subscr(ast, &indexast, 1, DTY(dtype + 1));
5344 } else {
5345 oldl = A_LOPG(ast);
5346 newl = replace_vector_subscript(oldl, indexast);
5347 if (oldl != newl) {
5348 ast = mk_member(oldl, A_MEMG(ast), dtype);
5349 }
5350 }
5351 break;
5352 case A_SUBSCR:
5353 /* go through the subscripts looking for a vector one */
5354 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
5355 nsubs = ASD_NDIM(asd);
5356 changes = FALSE;
5357 for (i = 0; i < nsubs; ++i) {
5358 int oldss, newss;
5359 oldss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
5360 newss = replace_vector_subscript(oldss, indexast);
5361 subs[i] = newss;
5362 if (newss != oldss)
5363 changes = TRUE;
5364 }
5365 if (changes) {
5366 ast = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(ast), subs, nsubs, dtype);
5367 }
5368 break;
5369
5370 case A_TRIPLE:
5371 /* change l:u:t into l+indexast */
5372 lb = A_LBDG(ast);
5373 if (lb == astb.i0) {
5374 ast = indexast;
5375 } else {
5376 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, lb, indexast, DT_INT);
5377 }
5378 break;
5379 default:
5380 interr("replace_vector_subscript: unexpected subscript operation",
5381 A_TYPEG(ast), 3);
5382 break;
5383 }
5384 return ast;
5385} /* replace_vector_subscript */
5386
5387/* this function expands f90 style derived type references into member
5388 * references, so the runtime doesn`t have to know how to print derived
5389 * types. Array of derived types will get dobegin/doend bracketing
5390 * the reference. This now handled both componentized and noncomponentized
5391 * derived types.
5392 */
5393
5394static IOL *
5395add_iolptrs(int dtype, SST *in_stkptr, int *mndscp)
5396{
5397 IOL *iolptr;
5398 IOL *startlist;
5399 IOL *endlist;
5400 int ast = 0;
5401 int sptr1, sptrm;
5402 int j, numdim;
5403 int derived_dtype, dtypem;
5404 int mem_id;
5405 int subs[7];
5406 SST *stkptr;
5407 SST tmpstk;
5408 IOL *dobegin;
5409 IOL *doend;
5410 IOL *tmp;
5411 int shp, leafast, rootast;
5412 int priv_err;
5413#if defined(DEBUG)
5414 int print_once = 0;
5415#endif
5416
5417 if (DTYG(dtype) != TY_DERIVED) {
5418 /* recursive member that is not itself a derived type */
5419 stkptr = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
5420 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, 0);
5421 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
5422 iolptr = (IOL *)getitem(0, sizeof(IOL));
5423 iolptr->next = NULL;
5424 *stkptr = *in_stkptr;
5425 iolptr->id = IE_EXPR;
5426 iolptr->element = stkptr;
5427 iolptr->l_std = 0;
5428 return iolptr;
5429 }
5430
5431 /* at a derived type; go through the members */
5432 startlist = NULL;
5433 endlist = NULL;
5434 switch (SST_IDG(in_stkptr)) {
5435 case S_IDENT:
5436 case S_DERIVED:
5437 sptr1 = SST_SYMG(in_stkptr);
5438 ast = mk_id(sptr1);
5439 break;
5440 case S_LVALUE:
5441 ast = SST_ASTG(in_stkptr);
5442 break;
5443 case S_EXPR:
5444 ast = SST_ASTG(in_stkptr);
5445 break;
5446 default:
5447 interr("add_iolptrs: unexpected semant stack type", SST_IDG(in_stkptr), 3);
5448 }
5449
5450 derived_dtype = DDTG(dtype);
5451
5452 dobegin = NULL;
5453 doend = NULL;
5454 /* TPR 2661:
5455 * if we have a reference x(i)%mem1(1:n)%mem2
5456 * the datatype is array(1:n) of dtypemem2
5457 * however, mem2 is a scalar, 'ast' is not a subscript.
5458 * So, if ast has the shape of its parent,
5459 * save the subtree from tail to the parent, reapply it later */
5460 leafast = ast;
5461 rootast = ast;
5462 while (1) {
5463 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM) {
5464 /* if parent is different shape, stop here */
5465 if (A_SHAPEG(ast) && A_SHAPEG(ast) == A_SHAPEG(A_PARENTG(ast))) {
5466 ast = A_PARENTG(ast);
5467 rootast = ast;
5468 continue;
5469 }
5470 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR) {
5471 int lop;
5472 lop = A_LOPG(ast);
5473 /* compare subscript with parent of A_MEM, if any */
5474 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_MEM && A_SHAPEG(ast) &&
5475 A_SHAPEG(ast) == A_SHAPEG(A_PARENTG(lop))) {
5476 ast = A_PARENTG(lop);
5477 rootast = ast;
5478 continue;
5479 }
5480 }
5481 break;
5482 }
5483 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY && ast && A_TYPEG(ast) != A_SUBSCR) {
5484 /* array of derived type. Rest of compiler doesn't handle
5485 * these 'inner' subscripts yet.
5486 * make a subscripted reference, the dobegins will be
5487 * thrown around at the end of this function */
5488 numdim = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
5489 for (j = 0; j < numdim; ++j) {
5490 tmp = get_dobegin(ADD_LWAST(dtype, j), ADD_UPAST(dtype, j), 0);
5491 dobegin = link_iollist(dobegin, tmp);
5492 subs[j] = mk_id(tmp->doinfo->index_var);
5493 tmp = get_doend(tmp->doinfo);
5494 doend = link_iollist(tmp, doend);
5495 }
5496 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, numdim, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast)));
5497 } else if (ast && A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR && (shp = A_SHAPEG(ast))) {
5498 /* we want to create/rewrite subscript and use dobegin/doend.
5499 * We may have to use doend/dobegin for internal triples, too.
5500 */
5501 int asd, numdim, i;
5502 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
5503 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd); /* get number of subscripts */
5504 for (i = 0; i < numdim; ++i) {
5505 int shpss, astss, sptrivar, astivar;
5506 int init, final, stride, normalize;
5507 normalize = 0;
5508 astss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
5509 shpss = A_SHAPEG(astss);
5510 if (A_TYPEG(astss) == A_TRIPLE) {
5511 init = A_LBDG(astss);
5512 final = A_UPBDG(astss);
5513 stride = A_STRIDEG(astss);
5514 if (stride == 0)
5515 stride = astb.i1;
5516 } else if (shpss) { /* better be one-dimensional */
5517 assert(SHD_NDIM(shpss) == 1,
5518 "add_iolptrs: subscript shape >1 dimension", SHD_NDIM(shpss), 3);
5519 init = SHD_LWB(shpss, 0);
5520 final = SHD_UPB(shpss, 0);
5521 stride = SHD_STRIDE(shpss, 0);
5522 if (A_TYPEG(astss) == A_SUBSCR) {
5523 int asdss;
5524 asdss = A_ASDG(astss);
5525 if (ASD_NDIM(asdss) != 1) {
5526 normalize = 1;
5527 }
5528 } else if (A_TYPEG(astss) != A_ID) {
5529 normalize = 1;
5530 }
5531 } else {
5532 init = 0;
5533 final = 0;
5534 stride = 0;
5535 }
5536 if (!init) {
5537 /* use the original subscript */
5538 subs[i] = astss;
5539 } else {
5540 /* create a DOINFO record for this dimension; the index
5541 * variable is a compiler-created temporary.
5542 */
5543 tmp = get_dobegin(init, final, stride);
5544 dobegin = link_iollist(dobegin, tmp);
5545 sptrivar = tmp->doinfo->index_var;
5546 if (normalize) {
5547 /* change limits from DO i=i,f,s to DO i=0,(f-i)/s,1 */
5548 int limit;
5549 limit = final;
5550 if (init != astb.i0) {
5551 limit = mk_binop(OP_SUB, limit, init, DT_INT);
5552 }
5553 if (stride != astb.i1) {
5554 limit = mk_binop(OP_DIV, limit, stride, DT_INT);
5555 }
5556 tmp->doinfo->init_expr = astb.i0;
5557 tmp->doinfo->limit_expr = limit;
5558 tmp->doinfo->step_expr = astb.i1;
5559 }
5560 tmp = get_doend(tmp->doinfo);
5561 doend = link_iollist(tmp, doend);
5562 /*
5563 * prepare the subscript for this dimension; it's just
5564 * a subscripted reference of the index vector and the
5565 * subscript is the DO index variable.
5566 */
5567 astivar = mk_id(sptrivar);
5568 if (normalize) {
5569 /* do something special */
5570 subs[i] = replace_vector_subscript(astss, astivar);
5571 } else if (A_TYPEG(astss) == A_TRIPLE) {
5572 subs[i] = astivar;
5573 } else if (A_TYPEG(astss) == A_ID) {
5574 /* subscript the array reference */
5575 subs[i] = mk_subscr(astss, &astivar, 1, DT_INT);
5576 } else if (A_TYPEG(astss) == A_SUBSCR) {
5577 subs[i] = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(astss), &astivar, 1, DT_INT);
5578 } else {
5579 /* no cases left */
5580 interr("add_iolptrs, unexpected subscript", A_TYPEG(astss), 3);
5581 }
5582 }
5583 }
5584 ast = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(ast), subs, numdim, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast)));
5585 }
5586 if (leafast != rootast) {
5587 ast = replace_ast_subtree(leafast, rootast, ast);
5588 }
5589
5590 priv_err = 0;
5591 for (sptrm = DTY(derived_dtype + 1); sptrm != NOSYM; sptrm = SYMLKG(sptrm)) {
5592 int i;
5593 if (is_tbp_or_final(sptrm)) {
5594#if DEBUG
5595 if (!print_once) {
5596 if (!sem.defined_io_seen) {
5597 if (BINDG(sptrm)) {
5598 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno,
5599 "Dubious use of derived type with "
5600 "type bound procedure in I/O statement",
5601 NULL);
5602 } else {
5603 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno,
5604 "Dubious use of derived type with "
5605 "final subroutine in I/O statement",
5606 NULL);
5607 }
5608 }
5609 print_once = 1;
5610 }
5611#endif
5612 continue; /* skip tbp member */
5613 }
5614 if (KINDG(sptrm) || LENPARMG(sptrm)) /* skip type parameters */
5615 continue;
5616 dtypem = DTYPEG(sptrm);
5617 if (PRIVATEG(sptrm) && test_private_dtype(ENCLDTYPEG(sptrm)) &&
5618 !sem.defined_io_seen) {
5619 priv_err = 1;
5620 }
5621 i = NMPTRG(sptrm);
5622 if (POINTERG(sptrm) && !sem.defined_io_seen) {
5623 error(453, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sym_of_ast(ast)), "");
5624 break;
5625 }
5626 mem_id = mkmember(derived_dtype, ast, i);
5627
5628 SST_IDP(&tmpstk, S_EXPR);
5629 SST_ASTP(&tmpstk, mem_id);
5630 SST_DTYPEP(&tmpstk, dtypem);
5631 SST_SHAPEP(&tmpstk, 0);
5632 SST_CVLENP(&tmpstk, 0);
5633 iolptr = add_iolptrs(dtypem, &tmpstk, mndscp);
5634 if (startlist) {
5635 endlist->next = iolptr;
5636 } else {
5637 /* first element(s) */
5638 startlist = iolptr;
5639 }
5640 endlist = find_end_iollist(iolptr);
5641
5642 /* FS#13258 If member is allocatable, skip pointer,offset,descriptor */
5643 if (ALLOCG(sptrm)) {
5644 int member = sptrm;
5645 while (SYMLKG(sptrm) == MIDNUMG(member) ||
5646 SYMLKG(sptrm) == PTROFFG(member) || SYMLKG(sptrm) == SDSCG(member))
5647 sptrm = SYMLKG(sptrm);
5648 }
5649 }
5650 if (dobegin) {
5651 startlist = link_iollist(dobegin, startlist);
5652 startlist = link_iollist(startlist, doend);
5653 }
5654 if (priv_err) {
5655 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
5656 "A derived type containing private components cannot be an I/O item",
5657 CNULL);
5658 }
5659 return startlist;
5660}
5661/* ------------------------------------------------------------------------ */
5662static void
5663get_derived_iolptrs(SST *result, int sptr1, SST *instkptr)
5664{
5665 IOL *iolptr;
5666 IOL *start;
5667
5668 start = add_iolptrs(SST_DTYPEG(instkptr), instkptr, NULL);
5669 iolptr = find_end_iollist(start);
5670 SST_BEGP(result, (ITEM *)start);
5671 SST_ENDP(result, (ITEM *)iolptr);
5672}
5673
5674static void
5675gen_derived_io(int sptr, FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn, int read)
5676{
5677 int bytfunc;
5678 int i;
5679
5680 if (!sptr) {
5681 /*
5682 * In general, should not get here if sptr is 0. But, there is
5683 * one case where this will happen -- the output item is
5684 * iso_c_binding:c_loc() and we would have already reported
5685 * the error,"A derived type containing private components cannot
5686 * be an I/O item" (search for c_loc earlier in this file).
5687 */
5688 return;
5689 }
5690 interr("gen_derived_io, f90 output not implemented", sptr, 2);
5691 bytfunc = mk_iofunc(rtlRtn, DT_INT, read ? 0 : INTENT_IN);
5692 i = mk_cval(size_of(DTYPEG(sptr)), DT_INT);
5693 (void)add_io_arg(astb.i1); /* length, stride */
5694 (void)add_io_arg(astb.i0);
5695 (void)add_io_arg(mk_id(sptr)); /* item */
5696 (void)add_io_arg(i); /* explicit item_length */
5697}
5698
5699/*
5700 * Compute last value of index variable:
5701 * index_var = max( (m2 - m1 + m3)/m3, 0)
5702 */
5703static void
5704gen_lastval(DOINFO *doinfo)
5705{
5706 int ast1, ast;
5707 int dtype;
5708
5709 ast1 = doinfo->count;
5710 dtype = DTYPEG(doinfo->index_var);
5711 ast = astb.i0;
5712 switch (dtype) {
5713 case DT_INT8:
5714 case DT_LOG8:
5715 dtype = DT_INT8;
5716 break;
5717 case DT_BINT:
5718 case DT_BLOG:
5719 dtype = DT_BINT;
5720 break;
5721 case DT_SINT:
5722 case DT_SLOG:
5723 dtype = DT_SINT;
5724 break;
5725 default:
5726 dtype = DT_INT4;
5727 break;
5728 }
5729 if (dtype != DT_INT4)
5730 ast = mk_convert(ast, dtype);
5731 ast1 = ast_intr(I_MAX, dtype, 2, ast1, ast);
5732 if (doinfo->step_expr)
5733 ast1 = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ast1, doinfo->step_expr, dtype);
5734 ast1 = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast1, doinfo->init_expr, dtype);
5735 ast = mk_assn_stmt(mk_id(doinfo->index_var), ast1, dtype);
5736 (void)add_stmt(ast);
5737}

5778
5779static int
5780gen_dtsfmt_args(int *iotype_ast, int *vlist_ast)
5781{
5782 int sptr;
5783 int tempbase, templen;
5784 int tast, baseast, asn;
5785 int dtype;
5786 ADSC *ad;
5787 tast = 0;
5788 asn = 1;
5789
5790 /* create deferchar for iotype , the callee will allocate it */
5791 sptr = getcctmp_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_VAR, DT_DEFERCHAR, SC_BASED);
5792
5793 ADJLENP(sptr, 1);
5794 ADDRTKNP(sptr, 1);
5795 SEQP(sptr, 1);
5796 ARGP(sptr, 1);
5797 tempbase = get_next_sym(SYMNAME(sptr), "cp");
5798 templen = get_next_sym(SYMNAME(sptr), "cl");
5799
5800 /* make the pointer points to sptr */
5801 STYPEP(tempbase, ST_VAR);
5802 DTYPEP(tempbase, DT_PTR);
5803 SCP(tempbase, io_sc);
5804 NODESCP(tempbase, 1);
5805 SEQP(sptr, 1);
5806
5807 /* set length variable */
5808 STYPEP(templen, ST_VAR);
5809 DTYPEP(templen, DT_INT);
5810 SCP(templen, io_sc);
5811
5812 MIDNUMP(sptr, tempbase);
5813 CVLENP(sptr, templen);
5814 tast = add_nullify_ast(mk_id(tempbase));
5815 add_stmt(tast);
5816
5817 *iotype_ast = mk_id(sptr);
5818 baseast = mk_id(tempbase);
5819
5820 if (XBIT(124, 0x10))
5821 dtype = get_array_dtype(1, DT_INT8);
5822 else
5823 dtype = get_array_dtype(1, DT_INT);
5824 sptr = getcctmp_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_ARRAY, dtype, SC_BASED);
5825 ALLOCP(sptr, 1);
5826 ADDRTKNP(sptr, 1);
5827 SEQP(sptr, 1);
5828 ARGP(sptr, 1);
5829 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
5830 ADD_DEFER(dtype) = 1;
5831 get_static_descriptor(sptr);
5832 get_all_descriptors(sptr);
5833 tempbase = MIDNUMG(sptr);
5834
5835 tast = add_nullify_ast(mk_id(tempbase));
5836 add_stmt(tast);
5837 *vlist_ast = mk_id(sptr);
5838
5839 return asn;
5840}
5841
5842static int
5843call_dtsfmt(int iotype_ast, int vlist_ast)
5844{
5845 int sptr, flagast;
5846 int tast, baseast, listast, lenast, arraydsc, asn;
5847 INT val[2];
5848
5849 val[0] = 0;
5850 if (XBIT(124, 0x10) && XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
5851 /* vlist is i8 and its descriptor is i8 */
5852 val[1] = 3;
5853 } else if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
5854 /* vlist is i4 and its descriptor is i8 */
5855 val[1] = 2;
5856 } else if (XBIT(124, 0x10)) {
5857 /* vlist is i8 and its descriptor is i4 */
5858 val[1] = 1;
5859 } else {
5860 /* vlist and its descriptor are i4 */
5861 val[1] = 0;
5862 }
5863
5864 lenast = mk_id(CVLENG(A_SPTRG(iotype_ast)));
5865 arraydsc = mk_id(SDSCG(A_SPTRG(vlist_ast)));
5866 listast = mk_id(MIDNUMG(A_SPTRG(vlist_ast)));
5867 baseast = mk_id(MIDNUMG(A_SPTRG(iotype_ast)));
5868 flagast = mk_id(getcon(val, DT_INT4));
5869
5870 if (is_read)
5871 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_dts_fmtr, DT_INT, 0);
5872 else
5873 sptr = mk_iofunc(RTE_f90io_dts_fmtw, DT_INT, 0);
5874
5875 tast = 0;
5876 tast = begin_call(A_FUNC, sptr, 5);
5877 (void)add_arg(baseast);
5878 (void)add_arg(listast);
5879 (void)add_arg(lenast);
5880 (void)add_arg(arraydsc);
5881 (void)add_arg(flagast);
5882 asn = mk_assn_stmt(ast_ioret(), tast, DT_INT);
5883 (void)add_stmt(asn);
5884 return asn;
5885}
5886
5887static ITEM *
5888gen_dtio_args(SST *stkptr, int arg1, int iotype_ast, int vlist_ast)
5889{
5890 ITEM *p, *arglist;
5891 INT v[2];
5892 int ast_type, iostat_ast, iomsg_ast, unit_ast;
5893 int sptr, tast;
5894 int argdtyp = DT_INT;
5895 if (XBIT(124, 0x10))
5896 argdtyp = DT_INT8;
5897
5898 /* dtv */
5899 p = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
5900 p->t.stkp = stkptr;
5901 p->next = NULL;
5902 p->ast = arg1;
5903 arglist = p;
5904
5905 /* unit */
5906 if (intern == TRUE) {
5907 v[0] = 0;
5908 v[1] = -1;
5909 unit_ast = mk_cnst(getcon(v, argdtyp));
5910
5911 } else {
5912 unit_ast = PTARG(PT_UNIT);
5913 if (A_DTYPEG(unit_ast) != argdtyp) {
5914 unit_ast = mk_convert(unit_ast, argdtyp);
5915 }
5916 }
5917 p->next = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
5918 p = p->next;
5919 p->t.stkp = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
5920 SST_ASTP(p->t.stkp, unit_ast);
5921 SST_DTYPEP(p->t.stkp, A_DTYPEG(unit_ast));
5922 ast_type = A_TYPEG(unit_ast);
5923 SST_SHAPEP(p->t.stkp, 0);
5924 if (ast_type == A_CNST) {
5925 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_CONST);
5926 SST_SYMP(p->t.stkp, A_SPTRG(unit_ast));
5927 SST_LSYMP(p->t.stkp, 0);
5928 SST_CVALP(p->t.stkp, CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(unit_ast)));
5929 } else if (ast_type == A_ID) {
5930 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_IDENT);
5931 SST_SYMP(p->t.stkp, A_SPTRG(unit_ast));
5932 mkident(p->t.stkp);
5933 } else {
5934 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_EXPR); /* need to check this */
5935 mkexpr(p->t.stkp);
5936 }
5937 p->ast = unit_ast;
5938
5939 if (fmttyp != FT_UNFORMATTED) {
5940 /* iotype */
5941 p->next = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
5942 p = p->next;
5943 p->t.stkp = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
5944 p->ast = iotype_ast;
5945 SST_ASTP(p->t.stkp, iotype_ast);
5946 SST_DTYPEP(p->t.stkp, A_DTYPEG(iotype_ast));
5947 SST_SYMP(p->t.stkp, A_SPTRG(iotype_ast));
5948 SST_PARENP(p->t.stkp, 0);
5949 SST_SHAPEP(p->t.stkp, 0);
5950 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_CONST);
5951
5952 /* v_list */
5953 if (vlist_ast == astb.i0) {
5954 /* make array of size 0 */
5955 /* set it as array size 0 first */
5956 int dtype = get_array_dtype(1, argdtyp);
5957 ADSC *ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
5958 AD_LWAST(ad, 0) = astb.i1;
5959 AD_LWBD(ad, 0) = astb.i1;
5960 AD_UPAST(ad, 0) = astb.i0;
5961 AD_UPBD(ad, 0) = astb.i0;
5962 AD_MLPYR(ad, 0) = astb.i1;
5963
5964 sptr = getcctmp_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_ARRAY, dtype, io_sc);
5965 vlist_ast = mk_id(sptr);
5966 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
5967 ARGP(sptr, 1);
5968 if (MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
5969 tast = add_nullify_ast(mk_id(MIDNUMG(sptr)));
5970 add_stmt(tast);
5971 }
5972 }
5973 p->next = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
5974 p = p->next;
5975 p->t.stkp = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
5976 p->next = NULL;
5977 p->ast = vlist_ast;
5978 SST_ASTP(p->t.stkp, vlist_ast);
5979 SST_DTYPEP(p->t.stkp, A_DTYPEG(vlist_ast));
5980 SST_SYMP(p->t.stkp, A_SPTRG(vlist_ast));
5981 SST_PARENP(p->t.stkp, 0);
5982 SST_SHAPEP(p->t.stkp, 0);
5983 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_IDENT);
5984 }
5985
5986 /* iostat */
5987 iostat_ast = PTARG(PT_IOSTAT);
5988 p->next = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
5989 p = p->next;
5990 p->t.stkp = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
5991 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_IDENT);
5992 if (iostat_ast == astb.i0) {
5993 sptr = getcctmp_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_VAR, argdtyp, io_sc);
5994 iostat_ast = mk_id(sptr);
5995 if (argdtyp != A_DTYPEG(astb.i0))
5996 tast = mk_assn_stmt(iostat_ast, mk_convert(astb.i0, argdtyp), argdtyp);
5997 else
5998 tast = mk_assn_stmt(iostat_ast, astb.i0, argdtyp);
5999 (void)add_stmt(tast);
6000 }
6001 p->ast = iostat_ast;
6002 SST_ASTP(p->t.stkp, iostat_ast);
6003 SST_DTYPEP(p->t.stkp, A_DTYPEG(iostat_ast));
6004 SST_SYMP(p->t.stkp, A_SPTRG(iostat_ast));
6005 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_IDENT);
6006 SST_PARENP(p->t.stkp, 0);
6007 SST_SHAPEP(p->t.stkp, 0);
6008
6009 /* iomsg */
6010 iomsg_ast = PTARG(PT_IOMSG);
6011 if (iomsg_ast == 0) {
6012 sptr = getcctmp_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_VAR, DT_CHAR, io_sc);
6013 iomsg_ast = mk_id(sptr);
6014 }
6015 p->next = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
6016 p = p->next;
6017 p->t.stkp = (SST *)getitem(0, sizeof(SST));
6018 p->next = ITEM_END;
6019 p->ast = iomsg_ast;
6020 SST_ASTP(p->t.stkp, iomsg_ast);
6021 SST_DTYPEP(p->t.stkp, A_DTYPEG(iomsg_ast));
6022 SST_SYMP(p->t.stkp, A_SPTRG(iomsg_ast));
6023 SST_IDP(p->t.stkp, S_IDENT);
6024 SST_PARENP(p->t.stkp, 0);
6025 SST_SHAPEP(p->t.stkp, 0);
6026
6027 return arglist;
6028}
6029
6030/* Returns an ast representing a call intended for a defined I/O subroutine.
6031 * fpstr = the function sptr returned from resolved_defined_io()
6032 * argcnt = number of arguments for the defined I/O subroutine
6033 * arglist = list of arguments. At the very least, argument 1, the derived
6034 * type variable, must be set when fsptr is a type bound procedure.
6035 */
6036static int
6037get_defined_io_call(int fsptr, int argcnt, ITEM *arglist)
6038{
6039 int ast, mem, i, dtv, dtv_sptr;
6040 ITEM *p;
6041
6042 if (CLASSG(fsptr) && VTABLEG(fsptr) && VTOFFG(fsptr)) {
6043
6044 /* generate tbp call */
6045
6046 dtv = arglist->ast;
6047 dtv_sptr = memsym_of_ast(dtv);
6048 ast = begin_call(A_CALL, fsptr, argcnt);
6049 if (!BINDG(fsptr) || !CCSYMG(fsptr)) {
6050 get_implementation(DTYPEG(dtv_sptr), fsptr, 0, &mem);
6051 fsptr = mem;
6052 }
6053 mem = mk_member(dtv, mk_id(fsptr), A_DTYPEG(dtv));
6054 A_LOPP(ast, mem);
6055
6056 /* add args in arglist */
6057 for (p = arglist, i = 0; i < argcnt; p = p->next) {
6058 add_arg(p->ast);
6059 ++i;
6060 }
6061 } else {
6062
6063 /* generate normal call */
6064
6065 ast = begin_call(A_CALL, fsptr, argcnt);
6066 for (p = arglist; p != ITEM_END; p = p->next) {
6067 add_arg(p->ast);
6068 }
6069 }
6070 return ast;
6071}
6072
6073static FtnRtlEnum
6074getBasicScalarRWRtn(LOGICAL is_read, FormatType fmttyp)
6075{
6076 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn = RTE_no_rtn;
6077
6078 if (is_read) {
6079 if (fmttyp == FT_UNFORMATTED)
6080 rtlRtn = unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_SWAPPED_IO_IDX].read;
6081 else if (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED)
6082 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_ldra;
6083 else
6084 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_fmt_reada;
6085 } else {
6086 if (fmttyp == FT_UNFORMATTED)
6087 rtlRtn = unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_SWAPPED_IO_IDX].write;
6088 else if (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED)
6089 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_ldwa;
6090 else
6091 rtlRtn = RTE_f90io_fmt_writea;
6092 }
6093 return rtlRtn;
6094}
6095
6096/* treat aggr. as byte stream */
6097static FtnRtlEnum
6098getAggrRWRtn(LOGICAL is_read)
6099{
6100 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn = RTE_no_rtn;
6101
6102 if (is_read) {
6103 rtlRtn = unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_RW_IDX].read;
6104 } else {
6105 rtlRtn = unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_RW_IDX].write;
6106 }
6107
6108 return rtlRtn;
6109}
6110
6111/*
6112 * For formatted & list-directed writes of certain
6113 * types of scalars, pass the scalars to the
6114 * run-time by value instead of by reference.
6115 * This at least removes one case of having to set
6116 * the scalar's ADDRTKN flag.
6117 */
6118static FtnRtlEnum
6119getWriteByDtypeRtn(int dtype, FormatType fmttyp)
6120{
6121 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn = RTE_no_rtn;
6122
6123 switch (dtype) {
6124 case DT_REAL4:
6125 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_f_ldw
6126 : RTE_f90io_sc_f_fmt_write;
6127 break;
6128 case DT_REAL8:
6129 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_d_ldw
6130 : RTE_f90io_sc_d_fmt_write;
6131 break;
6132#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
6133 case DT_QUAD:
6134 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_q_ldw
6135 : RTE_f90io_sc_q_fmt_write;
6136 break;
6137#endif
6138 case DT_INT8:
6139 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_l_ldw
6140 : RTE_f90io_sc_l_fmt_write;
6141 break;
6142 case DT_LOG8:
6143 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_l_ldw
6144 : RTE_f90io_sc_l_fmt_write;
6145 break;
6146 case DT_INT4:
6147 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_i_ldw
6148 : RTE_f90io_sc_i_fmt_write;
6149 break;
6150 case DT_BLOG:
6151 case DT_SLOG:
6152 case DT_LOG4:
6153 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_i_ldw
6154 : RTE_f90io_sc_i_fmt_write;
6155 break;
6156 case DT_CMPLX8:
6157 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_cf_ldw
6158 : RTE_f90io_sc_cf_fmt_write;
6159 break;
6160 case DT_CMPLX16:
6161 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_cd_ldw
6162 : RTE_f90io_sc_cd_fmt_write;
6163 break;
6164#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
6165 case DT_QCMPLX:
6166 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_cq_ldw
6167 : RTE_f90io_sc_cq_fmt_write;
6168 break;
6169#endif
6170 default:
6171 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
6172 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_ch_ldw
6173 : RTE_f90io_sc_ch_fmt_write;
6174 } else {
6175 rtlRtn = (fmttyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED) ? RTE_f90io_sc_ldw
6176 : RTE_f90io_sc_fmt_write;
6177 }
6178 break;
6179 }
6180
6181 return rtlRtn;
6182}
6183
6184static FtnRtlEnum
6185getArrayRWRtn(LOGICAL is_read, FormatType fmtTyp, int dtype, LOGICAL needDescr)
6186{
6187 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn = RTE_no_rtn;
6188
6189 if (needDescr) {
6190 if (is_read) {
6191 if (fmtTyp == FT_UNFORMATTED)
6192 rtlRtn = array_unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_SWAPPED_IO_IDX].read;
6193 else if (fmtTyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED)
6194 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_f90io_ldr64_aa : RTE_f90io_ldr_aa;
6195 else
6196 rtlRtn =
6197 (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_f90io_fmt_read64_aa : RTE_f90io_fmt_read_aa;
6198 } else {
6199 if (fmtTyp == FT_UNFORMATTED)
6200 rtlRtn = array_unf_nm[LARGE_ARRAY_IDX][BYTE_SWAPPED_IO_IDX].write;
6201 else if (fmtTyp == FT_LIST_DIRECTED)
6202 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_f90io_ldw64_aa : RTE_f90io_ldw_aa;
6203 else
6204 rtlRtn =
6205 (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_f90io_fmt_write64_aa : RTE_f90io_fmt_write_aa;
6206 }
6207 } else {
6208 if (is_read) {
6209 switch (fmtTyp) {
6210 case FT_UNFORMATTED:
6211 if (BYTE_SWAPPED_IO) {
6212 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_usw_read64 : RTE_io_usw_read;
6213 } else {
6214 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_unf_read64 : RTE_io_unf_read;
6215 }
6216 break;
6217 case FT_LIST_DIRECTED:
6218 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_ldr64 : RTE_io_ldr;
6219 break;
6220 default:
6221 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_fmt_read64 : RTE_io_fmt_read;
6222 break;
6223 }
6224 } else {
6225 switch (fmtTyp) {
6226 case FT_UNFORMATTED:
6227 if (BYTE_SWAPPED_IO) {
6228 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_usw_write64 : RTE_io_usw_write;
6229 } else {
6230 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_unf_write64 : RTE_io_unf_write;
6231 }
6232 break;
6233 case FT_LIST_DIRECTED:
6234 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_ldw64 : RTE_io_ldw;
6235 break;
6236 default:
6237 rtlRtn = (LARGE_ARRAY) ? RTE_io_fmt_write64 : RTE_io_fmt_write;
6238 break;
6239 }
6240 }
6241 }
6242
6243 return rtlRtn;
6244}
